75 * This bitmap is used to advertise the page sizes our hardware support

77 * physically contiguous memory regions it is mapping into page sizes
78 * that we support.

80 * 512GB Pages are not supported due to a hardware bug

139static inline int match_hid_uid(struct device *dev,
140 struct acpihid_map_entry *entry)
141{
142 const char *hid, *uid;
143
144 hid = acpi_device_hid(ACPI_COMPANION(dev));
145 uid = acpi_device_uid(ACPI_COMPANION(dev));
146
147 if (!hid || !(*hid))
148 return -ENODEV;
149
150 if (!uid || !(*uid))
151 return strcmp(hid, entry->hid);
152
153 if (!(*entry->uid))
154 return strcmp(hid, entry->hid);
155
156 return (strcmp(hid, entry->hid) || strcmp(uid, entry->uid));
157}
158
159static inline u16 get_pci_device_id(struct device *dev)
160{
161 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
162
163 return PCI_DEVID(pdev->bus->number, pdev->devfn);
164}
165
166static inline int get_acpihid_device_id(struct device *dev,
167 struct acpihid_map_entry **entry)
168{
169 struct acpihid_map_entry *p;
170
171 list_for_each_entry(p, &acpihid_map, list) {
172 if (!match_hid_uid(dev, p)) {
173 if (entry)
174 *entry = p;
175 return p->devid;
176 }
177 }
178 return -EINVAL;
179}
180
181static inline int get_device_id(struct device *dev)
182{
183 int devid;
184
185 if (dev_is_pci(dev))
186 devid = get_pci_device_id(dev);
187 else
188 devid = get_acpihid_device_id(dev, NULL);
189
190 return devid;
191}

204static struct iommu_dev_data *alloc_dev_data(u16 devid)
205{
206 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data;
207 unsigned long flags;
208
209 dev_data = kzalloc(sizeof(*dev_data), GFP_KERNEL);
210 if (!dev_data)
211 return NULL;
212
213 dev_data->devid = devid;
214
215 spin_lock_irqsave(&dev_data_list_lock, flags);
216 list_add_tail(&dev_data->dev_data_list, &dev_data_list);
217 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&dev_data_list_lock, flags);
218
219 ratelimit_default_init(&dev_data->rs);
220
221 return dev_data;
222}
223
224static struct iommu_dev_data *search_dev_data(u16 devid)
225{
226 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data;
227 unsigned long flags;
228
229 spin_lock_irqsave(&dev_data_list_lock, flags);
230 list_for_each_entry(dev_data, &dev_data_list, dev_data_list) {
231 if (dev_data->devid == devid)
232 goto out_unlock;
233 }
234
235 dev_data = NULL;
236
237out_unlock:
238 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&dev_data_list_lock, flags);
239
240 return dev_data;
241}

243static int __last_alias(struct pci_dev *pdev, u16 alias, void *data)
244{
245 *(u16 *)data = alias;
246 return 0;
247}
248
249static u16 get_alias(struct device *dev)
250{
251 struct pci_dev *pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
252 u16 devid, ivrs_alias, pci_alias;
253
254 /* The callers make sure that get_device_id() does not fail here */
255 devid = get_device_id(dev);
256 ivrs_alias = amd_iommu_alias_table[devid];
257 pci_for_each_dma_alias(pdev, __last_alias, &pci_alias);
258
259 if (ivrs_alias == pci_alias)
260 return ivrs_alias;
261
262 /*
263 * DMA alias showdown
264 *
265 * The IVRS is fairly reliable in telling us about aliases, but it
266 * can't know about every screwy device. If we don't have an IVRS
267 * reported alias, use the PCI reported alias. In that case we may
268 * still need to initialize the rlookup and dev_table entries if the
269 * alias is to a non-existent device.
270 */
271 if (ivrs_alias == devid) {
272 if (!amd_iommu_rlookup_table[pci_alias]) {
273 amd_iommu_rlookup_table[pci_alias] =
274 amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
275 memcpy(amd_iommu_dev_table[pci_alias].data,
276 amd_iommu_dev_table[devid].data,
277 sizeof(amd_iommu_dev_table[pci_alias].data));
278 }
279
280 return pci_alias;
281 }
282
283 pr_info("AMD-Vi: Using IVRS reported alias %02x:%02x.%d "
284 "for device %s[%04x:%04x], kernel reported alias "
285 "%02x:%02x.%d\n", PCI_BUS_NUM(ivrs_alias), PCI_SLOT(ivrs_alias),
286 PCI_FUNC(ivrs_alias), dev_name(dev), pdev->vendor, pdev->device,
287 PCI_BUS_NUM(pci_alias), PCI_SLOT(pci_alias),
288 PCI_FUNC(pci_alias));
289
290 /*
291 * If we don't have a PCI DMA alias and the IVRS alias is on the same
292 * bus, then the IVRS table may know about a quirk that we don't.
293 */
294 if (pci_alias == devid &&
295 PCI_BUS_NUM(ivrs_alias) == pdev->bus->number) {
296 pci_add_dma_alias(pdev, ivrs_alias & 0xff);
297 pr_info("AMD-Vi: Added PCI DMA alias %02x.%d for %s\n",
298 PCI_SLOT(ivrs_alias), PCI_FUNC(ivrs_alias),
299 dev_name(dev));
300 }
301
302 return ivrs_alias;
303}
304
305static struct iommu_dev_data *find_dev_data(u16 devid)
306{
307 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data;
308 struct amd_iommu *iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
309
310 dev_data = search_dev_data(devid);
311
312 if (dev_data == NULL) {
313 dev_data = alloc_dev_data(devid);
314 if (!dev_data)
315 return NULL;
316
317 if (translation_pre_enabled(iommu))
318 dev_data->defer_attach = true;
319 }
320
321 return dev_data;
322}
323
324struct iommu_dev_data *get_dev_data(struct device *dev)
325{
326 return dev->archdata.iommu;
327}
328EXPORT_SYMBOL(get_dev_data);

330/*
331* Find or create an IOMMU group for a acpihid device.
332*/
333static struct iommu_group *acpihid_device_group(struct device *dev)
334{
335 struct acpihid_map_entry *p, *entry = NULL;
336 int devid;
337
338 devid = get_acpihid_device_id(dev, &entry);
339 if (devid < 0)
340 return ERR_PTR(devid);
341
342 list_for_each_entry(p, &acpihid_map, list) {
343 if ((devid == p->devid) && p->group)
344 entry->group = p->group;
345 }
346
347 if (!entry->group)
348 entry->group = generic_device_group(dev);
349 else
350 iommu_group_ref_get(entry->group);
351
352 return entry->group;
353}

355static bool pci_iommuv2_capable(struct pci_dev *pdev)
356{
357 static const int caps[] = {
358 PCI_EXT_CAP_ID_ATS,
359 PCI_EXT_CAP_ID_PRI,
360 PCI_EXT_CAP_ID_PASID,
361 };
362 int i, pos;
363
364 for (i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
365 pos = pci_find_ext_capability(pdev, caps[i]);
366 if (pos == 0)
367 return false;
368 }
369
370 return true;
371}
372
373static bool pdev_pri_erratum(struct pci_dev *pdev, u32 erratum)
374{
375 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data;
376
377 dev_data = get_dev_data(&pdev->dev);
378
379 return dev_data->errata & (1 << erratum) ? true : false;
380}

382/*
383 * This function checks if the driver got a valid device from the caller to
384 * avoid dereferencing invalid pointers.
385 */
386static bool check_device(struct device *dev)
387{
388 int devid;
389
390 if (!dev || !dev->dma_mask)
391 return false;
392
393 devid = get_device_id(dev);
394 if (devid < 0)
395 return false;
396
397 /* Out of our scope? */
398 if (devid > amd_iommu_last_bdf)
399 return false;
400
401 if (amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid] == NULL)
402 return false;
403
404 return true;
405}

407static void init_iommu_group(struct device *dev)
408{
409 struct iommu_group *group;
410
411 group = iommu_group_get_for_dev(dev);
412 if (IS_ERR(group))
413 return;
414
415 iommu_group_put(group);
416}
417
418static int iommu_init_device(struct device *dev)
419{
420 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data;
421 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
422 int devid;
423
424 if (dev->archdata.iommu)
425 return 0;
426
427 devid = get_device_id(dev);
428 if (devid < 0)
429 return devid;
430
431 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
432
433 dev_data = find_dev_data(devid);
434 if (!dev_data)
435 return -ENOMEM;
436
437 dev_data->alias = get_alias(dev);
438
439 if (dev_is_pci(dev) && pci_iommuv2_capable(to_pci_dev(dev))) {
440 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
441
442 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[dev_data->devid];
443 dev_data->iommu_v2 = iommu->is_iommu_v2;
444 }
445
446 dev->archdata.iommu = dev_data;
447
448 iommu_device_link(&iommu->iommu, dev);
449
450 return 0;
451}
452
453static void iommu_ignore_device(struct device *dev)
454{
455 u16 alias;
456 int devid;
457
458 devid = get_device_id(dev);
459 if (devid < 0)
460 return;
461
462 alias = get_alias(dev);
463
464 memset(&amd_iommu_dev_table[devid], 0, sizeof(struct dev_table_entry));
465 memset(&amd_iommu_dev_table[alias], 0, sizeof(struct dev_table_entry));
466
467 amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid] = NULL;
468 amd_iommu_rlookup_table[alias] = NULL;
469}
470
471static void iommu_uninit_device(struct device *dev)
472{
473 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data;
474 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
475 int devid;
476
477 devid = get_device_id(dev);
478 if (devid < 0)
479 return;
480
481 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
482
483 dev_data = search_dev_data(devid);
484 if (!dev_data)
485 return;
486
487 if (dev_data->domain)
488 detach_device(dev);
489
490 iommu_device_unlink(&iommu->iommu, dev);
491
492 iommu_group_remove_device(dev);
493
494 /* Remove dma-ops */
495 dev->dma_ops = NULL;
496
497 /*
498 * We keep dev_data around for unplugged devices and reuse it when the
499 * device is re-plugged - not doing so would introduce a ton of races.
500 */
501}

509static void dump_dte_entry(u16 devid)
510{
511 int i;
512
513 for (i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
514 pr_err("AMD-Vi: DTE[%d]: %016llx\n", i,
515 amd_iommu_dev_table[devid].data[i]);
516}
517
518static void dump_command(unsigned long phys_addr)
519{
520 struct iommu_cmd *cmd = iommu_phys_to_virt(phys_addr);
521 int i;
522
523 for (i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
524 pr_err("AMD-Vi: CMD[%d]: %08x\n", i, cmd->data[i]);
525}

527static void amd_iommu_report_page_fault(u16 devid, u16 domain_id,
528 u64 address, int flags)
529{
530 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data = NULL;
531 struct pci_dev *pdev;
532
533 pdev = pci_get_bus_and_slot(PCI_BUS_NUM(devid), devid & 0xff);
534 if (pdev)
535 dev_data = get_dev_data(&pdev->dev);
536
537 if (dev_data && __ratelimit(&dev_data->rs)) {
538 dev_err(&pdev->dev, "AMD-Vi: Event logged [IO_PAGE_FAULT domain=0x%04x address=0x%016llx flags=0x%04x]\n",
539 domain_id, address, flags);
540 } else if (printk_ratelimit()) {
541 pr_err("AMD-Vi: Event logged [IO_PAGE_FAULT device=%02x:%02x.%x domain=0x%04x address=0x%016llx flags=0x%04x]\n",
542 PCI_BUS_NUM(devid), PCI_SLOT(devid), PCI_FUNC(devid),
543 domain_id, address, flags);
544 }
545
546 if (pdev)
547 pci_dev_put(pdev);
548}

550static void iommu_print_event(struct amd_iommu *iommu, void *__evt)
551{
552 int type, devid, domid, flags;
553 volatile u32 *event = __evt;
554 int count = 0;
555 u64 address;
556
557retry:
558 type = (event[1] >> EVENT_TYPE_SHIFT) & EVENT_TYPE_MASK;
559 devid = (event[0] >> EVENT_DEVID_SHIFT) & EVENT_DEVID_MASK;
560 domid = (event[1] >> EVENT_DOMID_SHIFT) & EVENT_DOMID_MASK;
561 flags = (event[1] >> EVENT_FLAGS_SHIFT) & EVENT_FLAGS_MASK;
562 address = (u64)(((u64)event[3]) << 32) | event[2];
563
564 if (type == 0) {
565 /* Did we hit the erratum? */
566 if (++count == LOOP_TIMEOUT) {
567 pr_err("AMD-Vi: No event written to event log\n");
568 return;
569 }
570 udelay(1);
571 goto retry;
572 }
573
574 if (type == EVENT_TYPE_IO_FAULT) {
575 amd_iommu_report_page_fault(devid, domid, address, flags);
576 return;
577 } else {
578 printk(KERN_ERR "AMD-Vi: Event logged [");
579 }
580
581 switch (type) {
582 case EVENT_TYPE_ILL_DEV:
583 printk("ILLEGAL_DEV_TABLE_ENTRY device=%02x:%02x.%x "
584 "address=0x%016llx flags=0x%04x]\n",
585 PCI_BUS_NUM(devid), PCI_SLOT(devid), PCI_FUNC(devid),
586 address, flags);
587 dump_dte_entry(devid);
588 break;
589 case EVENT_TYPE_DEV_TAB_ERR:
590 printk("DEV_TAB_HARDWARE_ERROR device=%02x:%02x.%x "
591 "address=0x%016llx flags=0x%04x]\n",
592 PCI_BUS_NUM(devid), PCI_SLOT(devid), PCI_FUNC(devid),
593 address, flags);
594 break;
595 case EVENT_TYPE_PAGE_TAB_ERR:
596 printk("PAGE_TAB_HARDWARE_ERROR device=%02x:%02x.%x "
597 "domain=0x%04x address=0x%016llx flags=0x%04x]\n",
598 PCI_BUS_NUM(devid), PCI_SLOT(devid), PCI_FUNC(devid),
599 domid, address, flags);
600 break;
601 case EVENT_TYPE_ILL_CMD:
602 printk("ILLEGAL_COMMAND_ERROR address=0x%016llx]\n", address);
603 dump_command(address);
604 break;
605 case EVENT_TYPE_CMD_HARD_ERR:
606 printk("COMMAND_HARDWARE_ERROR address=0x%016llx "
607 "flags=0x%04x]\n", address, flags);
608 break;
609 case EVENT_TYPE_IOTLB_INV_TO:
610 printk("IOTLB_INV_TIMEOUT device=%02x:%02x.%x "
611 "address=0x%016llx]\n",
612 PCI_BUS_NUM(devid), PCI_SLOT(devid), PCI_FUNC(devid),
613 address);
614 break;
615 case EVENT_TYPE_INV_DEV_REQ:
616 printk("INVALID_DEVICE_REQUEST device=%02x:%02x.%x "
617 "address=0x%016llx flags=0x%04x]\n",
618 PCI_BUS_NUM(devid), PCI_SLOT(devid), PCI_FUNC(devid),
619 address, flags);
620 break;
621 default:
622 printk(KERN_ERR "UNKNOWN type=0x%02x]\n", type);
623 }
624
625 memset(__evt, 0, 4 * sizeof(u32));
626}

628static void iommu_poll_events(struct amd_iommu *iommu)
629{
630 u32 head, tail;
631
632 head = readl(iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_EVT_HEAD_OFFSET);
633 tail = readl(iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_EVT_TAIL_OFFSET);
634
635 while (head != tail) {
636 iommu_print_event(iommu, iommu->evt_buf + head);
637 head = (head + EVENT_ENTRY_SIZE) % EVT_BUFFER_SIZE;
638 }
639
640 writel(head, iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_EVT_HEAD_OFFSET);
641}
642
643static void iommu_handle_ppr_entry(struct amd_iommu *iommu, u64 *raw)
644{
645 struct amd_iommu_fault fault;
646
647 if (PPR_REQ_TYPE(raw[0]) != PPR_REQ_FAULT) {
648 pr_err_ratelimited("AMD-Vi: Unknown PPR request received\n");
649 return;
650 }
651
652 fault.address = raw[1];
653 fault.pasid = PPR_PASID(raw[0]);
654 fault.device_id = PPR_DEVID(raw[0]);
655 fault.tag = PPR_TAG(raw[0]);
656 fault.flags = PPR_FLAGS(raw[0]);
657
658 atomic_notifier_call_chain(&ppr_notifier, 0, &fault);
659}
660
661static void iommu_poll_ppr_log(struct amd_iommu *iommu)
662{
663 u32 head, tail;
664
665 if (iommu->ppr_log == NULL)
666 return;
667
668 head = readl(iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_PPR_HEAD_OFFSET);
669 tail = readl(iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_PPR_TAIL_OFFSET);
670
671 while (head != tail) {
672 volatile u64 *raw;
673 u64 entry[2];
674 int i;
675
676 raw = (u64 *)(iommu->ppr_log + head);
677
678 /*
679 * Hardware bug: Interrupt may arrive before the entry is
680 * written to memory. If this happens we need to wait for the
681 * entry to arrive.
682 */
683 for (i = 0; i < LOOP_TIMEOUT; ++i) {
684 if (PPR_REQ_TYPE(raw[0]) != 0)
685 break;
686 udelay(1);
687 }
688
689 /* Avoid memcpy function-call overhead */
690 entry[0] = raw[0];
691 entry[1] = raw[1];
692
693 /*
694 * To detect the hardware bug we need to clear the entry
695 * back to zero.
696 */
697 raw[0] = raw[1] = 0UL;
698
699 /* Update head pointer of hardware ring-buffer */
700 head = (head + PPR_ENTRY_SIZE) % PPR_LOG_SIZE;
701 writel(head, iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_PPR_HEAD_OFFSET);
702
703 /* Handle PPR entry */
704 iommu_handle_ppr_entry(iommu, entry);
705
706 /* Refresh ring-buffer information */
707 head = readl(iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_PPR_HEAD_OFFSET);
708 tail = readl(iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_PPR_TAIL_OFFSET);
709 }
710}

722
723static void iommu_poll_ga_log(struct amd_iommu *iommu)
724{
725 u32 head, tail, cnt = 0;
726
727 if (iommu->ga_log == NULL)
728 return;
729
730 head = readl(iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_GA_HEAD_OFFSET);
731 tail = readl(iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_GA_TAIL_OFFSET);
732
733 while (head != tail) {
734 volatile u64 *raw;
735 u64 log_entry;
736
737 raw = (u64 *)(iommu->ga_log + head);
738 cnt++;
739
740 /* Avoid memcpy function-call overhead */
741 log_entry = *raw;
742
743 /* Update head pointer of hardware ring-buffer */
744 head = (head + GA_ENTRY_SIZE) % GA_LOG_SIZE;
745 writel(head, iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_GA_HEAD_OFFSET);
746
747 /* Handle GA entry */
748 switch (GA_REQ_TYPE(log_entry)) {
749 case GA_GUEST_NR:
750 if (!iommu_ga_log_notifier)
751 break;
752
753 pr_debug("AMD-Vi: %s: devid=%#x, ga_tag=%#x\n",
754 __func__, GA_DEVID(log_entry),
755 GA_TAG(log_entry));
756
757 if (iommu_ga_log_notifier(GA_TAG(log_entry)) != 0)
758 pr_err("AMD-Vi: GA log notifier failed.\n");
759 break;
760 default:
761 break;
762 }
763 }
764}
765#endif /* CONFIG_IRQ_REMAP */
766
767#define AMD_IOMMU_INT_MASK \
768 (MMIO_STATUS_EVT_INT_MASK | \
769 MMIO_STATUS_PPR_INT_MASK | \
770 MMIO_STATUS_GALOG_INT_MASK)
771
772irqreturn_t amd_iommu_int_thread(int irq, void *data)
773{
774 struct amd_iommu *iommu = (struct amd_iommu *) data;
775 u32 status = readl(iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_STATUS_OFFSET);
776
777 while (status & AMD_IOMMU_INT_MASK) {
778 /* Enable EVT and PPR and GA interrupts again */
779 writel(AMD_IOMMU_INT_MASK,
780 iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_STATUS_OFFSET);
781
782 if (status & MMIO_STATUS_EVT_INT_MASK) {
783 pr_devel("AMD-Vi: Processing IOMMU Event Log\n");
784 iommu_poll_events(iommu);
785 }
786
787 if (status & MMIO_STATUS_PPR_INT_MASK) {
788 pr_devel("AMD-Vi: Processing IOMMU PPR Log\n");
789 iommu_poll_ppr_log(iommu);
790 }
791
792#ifdef CONFIG_IRQ_REMAP
793 if (status & MMIO_STATUS_GALOG_INT_MASK) {
794 pr_devel("AMD-Vi: Processing IOMMU GA Log\n");
795 iommu_poll_ga_log(iommu);
796 }
797#endif
798
799 /*
800 * Hardware bug: ERBT1312
801 * When re-enabling interrupt (by writing 1
802 * to clear the bit), the hardware might also try to set
803 * the interrupt bit in the event status register.
804 * In this scenario, the bit will be set, and disable
805 * subsequent interrupts.
806 *
807 * Workaround: The IOMMU driver should read back the
808 * status register and check if the interrupt bits are cleared.
809 * If not, driver will need to go through the interrupt handler
810 * again and re-clear the bits
811 */
812 status = readl(iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_STATUS_OFFSET);
813 }
814 return IRQ_HANDLED;
815}
816
817irqreturn_t amd_iommu_int_handler(int irq, void *data)
818{
819 return IRQ_WAKE_THREAD;
820}

822/****************************************************************************
823 *
824 * IOMMU command queuing functions
825 *
826 ****************************************************************************/
827
828static int wait_on_sem(volatile u64 *sem)
829{
830 int i = 0;
831
832 while (*sem == 0 && i < LOOP_TIMEOUT) {
833 udelay(1);
834 i += 1;
835 }
836
837 if (i == LOOP_TIMEOUT) {
838 pr_alert("AMD-Vi: Completion-Wait loop timed out\n");
839 return -EIO;
840 }
841
842 return 0;
843}
844
845static void copy_cmd_to_buffer(struct amd_iommu *iommu,
846 struct iommu_cmd *cmd)
847{
848 u8 *target;
849
850 target = iommu->cmd_buf + iommu->cmd_buf_tail;
851
852 iommu->cmd_buf_tail += sizeof(*cmd);
853 iommu->cmd_buf_tail %= CMD_BUFFER_SIZE;
854
855 /* Copy command to buffer */
856 memcpy(target, cmd, sizeof(*cmd));
857
858 /* Tell the IOMMU about it */
859 writel(iommu->cmd_buf_tail, iommu->mmio_base + MMIO_CMD_TAIL_OFFSET);
860}
861
862static void build_completion_wait(struct iommu_cmd *cmd, u64 address)
863{
864 u64 paddr = iommu_virt_to_phys((void *)address);
865
866 WARN_ON(address & 0x7ULL);
867
868 memset(cmd, 0, sizeof(*cmd));
869 cmd->data[0] = lower_32_bits(paddr) | CMD_COMPL_WAIT_STORE_MASK;
870 cmd->data[1] = upper_32_bits(paddr);
871 cmd->data[2] = 1;
872 CMD_SET_TYPE(cmd, CMD_COMPL_WAIT);
873}
874
875static void build_inv_dte(struct iommu_cmd *cmd, u16 devid)
876{
877 memset(cmd, 0, sizeof(*cmd));
878 cmd->data[0] = devid;
879 CMD_SET_TYPE(cmd, CMD_INV_DEV_ENTRY);
880}
881
882static void build_inv_iommu_pages(struct iommu_cmd *cmd, u64 address,
883 size_t size, u16 domid, int pde)
884{
885 u64 pages;
886 bool s;
887
888 pages = iommu_num_pages(address, size, PAGE_SIZE);
889 s = false;
890
891 if (pages > 1) {
892 /*
893 * If we have to flush more than one page, flush all
894 * TLB entries for this domain
895 */
896 address = CMD_INV_IOMMU_ALL_PAGES_ADDRESS;
897 s = true;
898 }
899
900 address &= PAGE_MASK;
901
902 memset(cmd, 0, sizeof(*cmd));
903 cmd->data[1] |= domid;
904 cmd->data[2] = lower_32_bits(address);
905 cmd->data[3] = upper_32_bits(address);
906 CMD_SET_TYPE(cmd, CMD_INV_IOMMU_PAGES);
907 if (s) /* size bit - we flush more than one 4kb page */
908 cmd->data[2] |= CMD_INV_IOMMU_PAGES_SIZE_MASK;
909 if (pde) /* PDE bit - we want to flush everything, not only the PTEs */
910 cmd->data[2] |= CMD_INV_IOMMU_PAGES_PDE_MASK;
911}
912
913static void build_inv_iotlb_pages(struct iommu_cmd *cmd, u16 devid, int qdep,
914 u64 address, size_t size)
915{
916 u64 pages;
917 bool s;
918
919 pages = iommu_num_pages(address, size, PAGE_SIZE);
920 s = false;
921
922 if (pages > 1) {
923 /*
924 * If we have to flush more than one page, flush all
925 * TLB entries for this domain
926 */
927 address = CMD_INV_IOMMU_ALL_PAGES_ADDRESS;
928 s = true;
929 }
930
931 address &= PAGE_MASK;
932
933 memset(cmd, 0, sizeof(*cmd));
934 cmd->data[0] = devid;
935 cmd->data[0] |= (qdep & 0xff) << 24;
936 cmd->data[1] = devid;
937 cmd->data[2] = lower_32_bits(address);
938 cmd->data[3] = upper_32_bits(address);
939 CMD_SET_TYPE(cmd, CMD_INV_IOTLB_PAGES);
940 if (s)
941 cmd->data[2] |= CMD_INV_IOMMU_PAGES_SIZE_MASK;
942}
943
944static void build_inv_iommu_pasid(struct iommu_cmd *cmd, u16 domid, int pasid,
945 u64 address, bool size)
946{
947 memset(cmd, 0, sizeof(*cmd));
948
949 address &= ~(0xfffULL);
950
951 cmd->data[0] = pasid;
952 cmd->data[1] = domid;
953 cmd->data[2] = lower_32_bits(address);
954 cmd->data[3] = upper_32_bits(address);
955 cmd->data[2] |= CMD_INV_IOMMU_PAGES_PDE_MASK;
956 cmd->data[2] |= CMD_INV_IOMMU_PAGES_GN_MASK;
957 if (size)
958 cmd->data[2] |= CMD_INV_IOMMU_PAGES_SIZE_MASK;
959 CMD_SET_TYPE(cmd, CMD_INV_IOMMU_PAGES);
960}
961
962static void build_inv_iotlb_pasid(struct iommu_cmd *cmd, u16 devid, int pasid,
963 int qdep, u64 address, bool size)
964{
965 memset(cmd, 0, sizeof(*cmd));
966
967 address &= ~(0xfffULL);
968
969 cmd->data[0] = devid;
970 cmd->data[0] |= ((pasid >> 8) & 0xff) << 16;
971 cmd->data[0] |= (qdep & 0xff) << 24;
972 cmd->data[1] = devid;
973 cmd->data[1] |= (pasid & 0xff) << 16;
974 cmd->data[2] = lower_32_bits(address);
975 cmd->data[2] |= CMD_INV_IOMMU_PAGES_GN_MASK;
976 cmd->data[3] = upper_32_bits(address);
977 if (size)
978 cmd->data[2] |= CMD_INV_IOMMU_PAGES_SIZE_MASK;
979 CMD_SET_TYPE(cmd, CMD_INV_IOTLB_PAGES);
980}
981
982static void build_complete_ppr(struct iommu_cmd *cmd, u16 devid, int pasid,
983 int status, int tag, bool gn)
984{
985 memset(cmd, 0, sizeof(*cmd));
986
987 cmd->data[0] = devid;
988 if (gn) {
989 cmd->data[1] = pasid;
990 cmd->data[2] = CMD_INV_IOMMU_PAGES_GN_MASK;
991 }
992 cmd->data[3] = tag & 0x1ff;
993 cmd->data[3] |= (status & PPR_STATUS_MASK) << PPR_STATUS_SHIFT;
994
995 CMD_SET_TYPE(cmd, CMD_COMPLETE_PPR);
996}

998static void build_inv_all(struct iommu_cmd *cmd)
999{
1000 memset(cmd, 0, sizeof(*cmd));
1001 CMD_SET_TYPE(cmd, CMD_INV_ALL);
1002}

1004static void build_inv_irt(struct iommu_cmd *cmd, u16 devid)
1005{
1006 memset(cmd, 0, sizeof(*cmd));
1007 cmd->data[0] = devid;
1008 CMD_SET_TYPE(cmd, CMD_INV_IRT);
1009}

1011/*
1012 * Writes the command to the IOMMUs command buffer and informs the
1013 * hardware about the new command.
1014 */
1015static int __iommu_queue_command_sync(struct amd_iommu *iommu,
1016 struct iommu_cmd *cmd,
1017 bool sync)
1018{
1019 unsigned int count = 0;
1020 u32 left, next_tail;
1021
1022 next_tail = (iommu->cmd_buf_tail + sizeof(*cmd)) % CMD_BUFFER_SIZE;
1023again:
1024 left = (iommu->cmd_buf_head - next_tail) % CMD_BUFFER_SIZE;
1025
1026 if (left <= 0x20) {
1027 /* Skip udelay() the first time around */
1028 if (count++) {
1029 if (count == LOOP_TIMEOUT) {
1030 pr_err("AMD-Vi: Command buffer timeout\n");
1031 return -EIO;
1032 }
1033
1034 udelay(1);
1035 }
1036
1037 /* Update head and recheck remaining space */
1038 iommu->cmd_buf_head = readl(iommu->mmio_base +
1039 MMIO_CMD_HEAD_OFFSET);
1040
1041 goto again;
1042 }
1043
1044 copy_cmd_to_buffer(iommu, cmd);
1045
1046 /* Do we need to make sure all commands are processed? */
1047 iommu->need_sync = sync;
1048
1049 return 0;
1050}
1051
1052static int iommu_queue_command_sync(struct amd_iommu *iommu,
1053 struct iommu_cmd *cmd,
1054 bool sync)
1055{
1056 unsigned long flags;
1057 int ret;
1058
1059 spin_lock_irqsave(&iommu->lock, flags);
1060 ret = __iommu_queue_command_sync(iommu, cmd, sync);
1061 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&iommu->lock, flags);
1062
1063 return ret;
1064}
1065
1066static int iommu_queue_command(struct amd_iommu *iommu, struct iommu_cmd *cmd)
1067{
1068 return iommu_queue_command_sync(iommu, cmd, true);
1069}
1070
1071/*
1072 * This function queues a completion wait command into the command
1073 * buffer of an IOMMU
1074 */
1075static int iommu_completion_wait(struct amd_iommu *iommu)
1076{
1077 struct iommu_cmd cmd;
1078 unsigned long flags;
1079 int ret;
1080
1081 if (!iommu->need_sync)
1082 return 0;
1083
1084
1085 build_completion_wait(&cmd, (u64)&iommu->cmd_sem);
1086
1087 spin_lock_irqsave(&iommu->lock, flags);
1088
1089 iommu->cmd_sem = 0;
1090
1091 ret = __iommu_queue_command_sync(iommu, &cmd, false);
1092 if (ret)
1093 goto out_unlock;
1094
1095 ret = wait_on_sem(&iommu->cmd_sem);
1096
1097out_unlock:
1098 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&iommu->lock, flags);
1099
1100 return ret;
1101}

1180/*
1181 * Command send function for flushing on-device TLB
1182 */
1183static int device_flush_iotlb(struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data,
1184 u64 address, size_t size)
1185{

1188 int qdep;
1189
1190 qdep = dev_data->ats.qdep;
1191 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[dev_data->devid];

1198/*
1199 * Command send function for invalidating a device table entry
1200 */
1201static int device_flush_dte(struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data)
1202{
1203 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
1204 u16 alias;
1205 int ret;
1206
1207 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[dev_data->devid];
1208 alias = dev_data->alias;
1209
1210 ret = iommu_flush_dte(iommu, dev_data->devid);
1211 if (!ret && alias != dev_data->devid)
1212 ret = iommu_flush_dte(iommu, alias);
1213 if (ret)
1214 return ret;
1215
1216 if (dev_data->ats.enabled)
1217 ret = device_flush_iotlb(dev_data, 0, ~0UL);
1218
1219 return ret;
1220}

1222/*
1223 * TLB invalidation function which is called from the mapping functions.
1224 * It invalidates a single PTE if the range to flush is within a single
1225 * page. Otherwise it flushes the whole TLB of the IOMMU.
1226 */
1227static void __domain_flush_pages(struct protection_domain *domain,
1228 u64 address, size_t size, int pde)
1229{
1230 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data;
1231 struct iommu_cmd cmd;
1232 int ret = 0, i;
1233
1234 build_inv_iommu_pages(&cmd, address, size, domain->id, pde);
1235
1236 for (i = 0; i < amd_iommu_get_num_iommus(); ++i) {
1237 if (!domain->dev_iommu[i])
1238 continue;
1239
1240 /*
1241 * Devices of this domain are behind this IOMMU
1242 * We need a TLB flush
1243 */
1244 ret |= iommu_queue_command(amd_iommus[i], &cmd);
1245 }
1246
1247 list_for_each_entry(dev_data, &domain->dev_list, list) {
1248
1249 if (!dev_data->ats.enabled)
1250 continue;
1251
1252 ret |= device_flush_iotlb(dev_data, address, size);
1253 }
1254
1255 WARN_ON(ret);
1256}
1257
1258static void domain_flush_pages(struct protection_domain *domain,
1259 u64 address, size_t size)
1260{
1261 __domain_flush_pages(domain, address, size, 0);
1262}

1264/* Flush the whole IO/TLB for a given protection domain */
1265static void domain_flush_tlb(struct protection_domain *domain)
1266{
1267 __domain_flush_pages(domain, 0, CMD_INV_IOMMU_ALL_PAGES_ADDRESS, 0);
1268}

1270/* Flush the whole IO/TLB for a given protection domain - including PDE */
1271static void domain_flush_tlb_pde(struct protection_domain *domain)
1272{
1273 __domain_flush_pages(domain, 0, CMD_INV_IOMMU_ALL_PAGES_ADDRESS, 1);
1274}
1275
1276static void domain_flush_complete(struct protection_domain *domain)
1277{
1278 int i;
1279
1280 for (i = 0; i < amd_iommu_get_num_iommus(); ++i) {
1281 if (domain && !domain->dev_iommu[i])
1282 continue;
1283
1284 /*
1285 * Devices of this domain are behind this IOMMU
1286 * We need to wait for completion of all commands.
1287 */
1288 iommu_completion_wait(amd_iommus[i]);
1289 }
1290}

1304/****************************************************************************
1305 *
1306 * The functions below are used the create the page table mappings for
1307 * unity mapped regions.
1308 *
1309 ****************************************************************************/
1310
1311/*
1312 * This function is used to add another level to an IO page table. Adding
1313 * another level increases the size of the address space by 9 bits to a size up
1314 * to 64 bits.
1315 */
1316static bool increase_address_space(struct protection_domain *domain,
1317 gfp_t gfp)
1318{
1319 u64 *pte;
1320
1321 if (domain->mode == PAGE_MODE_6_LEVEL)
1322 /* address space already 64 bit large */
1323 return false;
1324
1325 pte = (void *)get_zeroed_page(gfp);
1326 if (!pte)
1327 return false;
1328
1329 *pte = PM_LEVEL_PDE(domain->mode,
1330 iommu_virt_to_phys(domain->pt_root));
1331 domain->pt_root = pte;
1332 domain->mode += 1;
1333 domain->updated = true;
1334
1335 return true;
1336}
1337
1338static u64 *alloc_pte(struct protection_domain *domain,
1339 unsigned long address,
1340 unsigned long page_size,
1341 u64 **pte_page,
1342 gfp_t gfp)
1343{
1344 int level, end_lvl;
1345 u64 *pte, *page;
1346
1347 BUG_ON(!is_power_of_2(page_size));
1348
1349 while (address > PM_LEVEL_SIZE(domain->mode))
1350 increase_address_space(domain, gfp);
1351
1352 level = domain->mode - 1;
1353 pte = &domain->pt_root[PM_LEVEL_INDEX(level, address)];
1354 address = PAGE_SIZE_ALIGN(address, page_size);
1355 end_lvl = PAGE_SIZE_LEVEL(page_size);
1356
1357 while (level > end_lvl) {
1358 u64 __pte, __npte;
1359
1360 __pte = *pte;
1361
1362 if (!IOMMU_PTE_PRESENT(__pte)) {
1363 page = (u64 *)get_zeroed_page(gfp);
1364 if (!page)
1365 return NULL;
1366
1367 __npte = PM_LEVEL_PDE(level, iommu_virt_to_phys(page));
1368
1369 /* pte could have been changed somewhere. */
1370 if (cmpxchg64(pte, __pte, __npte) != __pte) {
1371 free_page((unsigned long)page);
1372 continue;
1373 }
1374 }
1375
1376 /* No level skipping support yet */
1377 if (PM_PTE_LEVEL(*pte) != level)
1378 return NULL;
1379
1380 level -= 1;
1381
1382 pte = IOMMU_PTE_PAGE(*pte);
1383
1384 if (pte_page && level == end_lvl)
1385 *pte_page = pte;
1386
1387 pte = &pte[PM_LEVEL_INDEX(level, address)];
1388 }
1389
1390 return pte;
1391}
1392
1393/*
1394 * This function checks if there is a PTE for a given dma address. If
1395 * there is one, it returns the pointer to it.
1396 */
1397static u64 *fetch_pte(struct protection_domain *domain,
1398 unsigned long address,
1399 unsigned long *page_size)
1400{
1401 int level;
1402 u64 *pte;
1403
1404 if (address > PM_LEVEL_SIZE(domain->mode))
1405 return NULL;
1406
1407 level = domain->mode - 1;
1408 pte = &domain->pt_root[PM_LEVEL_INDEX(level, address)];
1409 *page_size = PTE_LEVEL_PAGE_SIZE(level);
1410
1411 while (level > 0) {
1412
1413 /* Not Present */
1414 if (!IOMMU_PTE_PRESENT(*pte))
1415 return NULL;
1416
1417 /* Large PTE */
1418 if (PM_PTE_LEVEL(*pte) == 7 ||
1419 PM_PTE_LEVEL(*pte) == 0)
1420 break;
1421
1422 /* No level skipping support yet */
1423 if (PM_PTE_LEVEL(*pte) != level)
1424 return NULL;
1425
1426 level -= 1;
1427
1428 /* Walk to the next level */
1429 pte = IOMMU_PTE_PAGE(*pte);
1430 pte = &pte[PM_LEVEL_INDEX(level, address)];
1431 *page_size = PTE_LEVEL_PAGE_SIZE(level);
1432 }
1433
1434 if (PM_PTE_LEVEL(*pte) == 0x07) {
1435 unsigned long pte_mask;
1436
1437 /*
1438 * If we have a series of large PTEs, make
1439 * sure to return a pointer to the first one.
1440 */
1441 *page_size = pte_mask = PTE_PAGE_SIZE(*pte);
1442 pte_mask = ~((PAGE_SIZE_PTE_COUNT(pte_mask) << 3) - 1);
1443 pte = (u64 *)(((unsigned long)pte) & pte_mask);
1444 }
1445
1446 return pte;
1447}
1448
1449/*
1450 * Generic mapping functions. It maps a physical address into a DMA
1451 * address space. It allocates the page table pages if necessary.
1452 * In the future it can be extended to a generic mapping function
1453 * supporting all features of AMD IOMMU page tables like level skipping
1454 * and full 64 bit address spaces.
1455 */
1456static int iommu_map_page(struct protection_domain *dom,
1457 unsigned long bus_addr,
1458 unsigned long phys_addr,
1459 unsigned long page_size,
1460 int prot,
1461 gfp_t gfp)
1462{
1463 u64 __pte, *pte;
1464 int i, count;
1465
1466 BUG_ON(!IS_ALIGNED(bus_addr, page_size));
1467 BUG_ON(!IS_ALIGNED(phys_addr, page_size));
1468
1469 if (!(prot & IOMMU_PROT_MASK))
1470 return -EINVAL;
1471
1472 count = PAGE_SIZE_PTE_COUNT(page_size);
1473 pte = alloc_pte(dom, bus_addr, page_size, NULL, gfp);
1474
1475 if (!pte)
1476 return -ENOMEM;
1477
1478 for (i = 0; i < count; ++i)
1479 if (IOMMU_PTE_PRESENT(pte[i]))
1480 return -EBUSY;
1481
1482 if (count > 1) {
1483 __pte = PAGE_SIZE_PTE(__sme_set(phys_addr), page_size);
1484 __pte |= PM_LEVEL_ENC(7) | IOMMU_PTE_PR | IOMMU_PTE_FC;
1485 } else
1486 __pte = __sme_set(phys_addr) | IOMMU_PTE_PR | IOMMU_PTE_FC;
1487
1488 if (prot & IOMMU_PROT_IR)
1489 __pte |= IOMMU_PTE_IR;
1490 if (prot & IOMMU_PROT_IW)
1491 __pte |= IOMMU_PTE_IW;
1492
1493 for (i = 0; i < count; ++i)
1494 pte[i] = __pte;
1495
1496 update_domain(dom);
1497
1498 return 0;
1499}
1500
1501static unsigned long iommu_unmap_page(struct protection_domain *dom,
1502 unsigned long bus_addr,
1503 unsigned long page_size)
1504{
1505 unsigned long long unmapped;
1506 unsigned long unmap_size;
1507 u64 *pte;
1508
1509 BUG_ON(!is_power_of_2(page_size));
1510
1511 unmapped = 0;
1512
1513 while (unmapped < page_size) {
1514
1515 pte = fetch_pte(dom, bus_addr, &unmap_size);
1516
1517 if (pte) {
1518 int i, count;
1519
1520 count = PAGE_SIZE_PTE_COUNT(unmap_size);
1521 for (i = 0; i < count; i++)
1522 pte[i] = 0ULL;
1523 }
1524
1525 bus_addr = (bus_addr & ~(unmap_size - 1)) + unmap_size;
1526 unmapped += unmap_size;
1527 }
1528
1529 BUG_ON(unmapped && !is_power_of_2(unmapped));
1530
1531 return unmapped;
1532}

1535 *
1536 * The next functions belong to the address allocator for the dma_ops
1537 * interface functions.

1541
1542static unsigned long dma_ops_alloc_iova(struct device *dev,
1543 struct dma_ops_domain *dma_dom,
1544 unsigned int pages, u64 dma_mask)
1545{
1546 unsigned long pfn = 0;
1547
1548 pages = __roundup_pow_of_two(pages);
1549
1550 if (dma_mask > DMA_BIT_MASK(32))
1551 pfn = alloc_iova_fast(&dma_dom->iovad, pages,
1552 IOVA_PFN(DMA_BIT_MASK(32)));
1553
1554 if (!pfn)
1555 pfn = alloc_iova_fast(&dma_dom->iovad, pages, IOVA_PFN(dma_mask));
1556
1557 return (pfn << PAGE_SHIFT);
1558}
1559
1560static void dma_ops_free_iova(struct dma_ops_domain *dma_dom,
1561 unsigned long address,
1562 unsigned int pages)
1563{
1564 pages = __roundup_pow_of_two(pages);
1565 address >>= PAGE_SHIFT;
1566
1567 free_iova_fast(&dma_dom->iovad, address, pages);
1568}

1594 * protection domain list

1605static u16 domain_id_alloc(void)
1606{
1607 unsigned long flags;
1608 int id;
1609
1610 write_lock_irqsave(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
1611 id = find_first_zero_bit(amd_iommu_pd_alloc_bitmap, MAX_DOMAIN_ID);
1612 BUG_ON(id == 0);
1613 if (id > 0 && id < MAX_DOMAIN_ID)
1614 __set_bit(id, amd_iommu_pd_alloc_bitmap);
1615 else
1616 id = 0;
1617 write_unlock_irqrestore(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
1618
1619 return id;
1620}

1622static void domain_id_free(int id)
1623{
1624 unsigned long flags;
1625
1626 write_lock_irqsave(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
1627 if (id > 0 && id < MAX_DOMAIN_ID)
1628 __clear_bit(id, amd_iommu_pd_alloc_bitmap);
1629 write_unlock_irqrestore(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
1630}

1632#define DEFINE_FREE_PT_FN(LVL, FN) \
1633static void free_pt_##LVL (unsigned long __pt) \
1634{ \
1635 unsigned long p; \
1636 u64 *pt; \
1637 int i; \
1638 \
1639 pt = (u64 *)__pt; \
1640 \
1641 for (i = 0; i < 512; ++i) { \
1642 /* PTE present? */ \
1643 if (!IOMMU_PTE_PRESENT(pt[i])) \
1644 continue; \
1645 \
1646 /* Large PTE? */ \
1647 if (PM_PTE_LEVEL(pt[i]) == 0 || \
1648 PM_PTE_LEVEL(pt[i]) == 7) \
1649 continue; \
1650 \
1651 p = (unsigned long)IOMMU_PTE_PAGE(pt[i]); \
1652 FN(p); \
1653 } \
1654 free_page((unsigned long)pt); \
1655}
1656
1657DEFINE_FREE_PT_FN(l2, free_page)
1658DEFINE_FREE_PT_FN(l3, free_pt_l2)
1659DEFINE_FREE_PT_FN(l4, free_pt_l3)
1660DEFINE_FREE_PT_FN(l5, free_pt_l4)
1661DEFINE_FREE_PT_FN(l6, free_pt_l5)
1662
1663static void free_pagetable(struct protection_domain *domain)
1664{
1665 unsigned long root = (unsigned long)domain->pt_root;
1666
1667 switch (domain->mode) {
1668 case PAGE_MODE_NONE:
1669 break;
1670 case PAGE_MODE_1_LEVEL:
1671 free_page(root);
1672 break;
1673 case PAGE_MODE_2_LEVEL:
1674 free_pt_l2(root);
1675 break;
1676 case PAGE_MODE_3_LEVEL:
1677 free_pt_l3(root);
1678 break;
1679 case PAGE_MODE_4_LEVEL:
1680 free_pt_l4(root);
1681 break;
1682 case PAGE_MODE_5_LEVEL:
1683 free_pt_l5(root);
1684 break;
1685 case PAGE_MODE_6_LEVEL:
1686 free_pt_l6(root);
1687 break;
1688 default:
1689 BUG();
1690 }
1691}
1692
1693static void free_gcr3_tbl_level1(u64 *tbl)
1694{
1695 u64 *ptr;
1696 int i;
1697
1698 for (i = 0; i < 512; ++i) {
1699 if (!(tbl[i] & GCR3_VALID))
1700 continue;
1701
1702 ptr = iommu_phys_to_virt(tbl[i] & PAGE_MASK);
1703
1704 free_page((unsigned long)ptr);
1705 }
1706}
1707
1708static void free_gcr3_tbl_level2(u64 *tbl)
1709{
1710 u64 *ptr;
1711 int i;
1712
1713 for (i = 0; i < 512; ++i) {
1714 if (!(tbl[i] & GCR3_VALID))
1715 continue;
1716
1717 ptr = iommu_phys_to_virt(tbl[i] & PAGE_MASK);
1718
1719 free_gcr3_tbl_level1(ptr);
1720 }
1721}
1722
1723static void free_gcr3_table(struct protection_domain *domain)
1724{
1725 if (domain->glx == 2)
1726 free_gcr3_tbl_level2(domain->gcr3_tbl);
1727 else if (domain->glx == 1)
1728 free_gcr3_tbl_level1(domain->gcr3_tbl);
1729 else
1730 BUG_ON(domain->glx != 0);
1731
1732 free_page((unsigned long)domain->gcr3_tbl);
1733}

1735static void dma_ops_domain_flush_tlb(struct dma_ops_domain *dom)
1736{
1737 domain_flush_tlb(&dom->domain);
1738 domain_flush_complete(&dom->domain);
1739}

1741static void iova_domain_flush_tlb(struct iova_domain *iovad)
1742{
1743 struct dma_ops_domain *dom;
1744
1745 dom = container_of(iovad, struct dma_ops_domain, iovad);
1746
1747 dma_ops_domain_flush_tlb(dom);
1748}

1750/*
1751 * Free a domain, only used if something went wrong in the
1752 * allocation path and we need to free an already allocated page table
1753 */
1754static void dma_ops_domain_free(struct dma_ops_domain *dom)
1755{
1756 if (!dom)
1757 return;
1758
1759 del_domain_from_list(&dom->domain);
1760
1761 put_iova_domain(&dom->iovad);
1762
1763 free_pagetable(&dom->domain);
1764
1765 if (dom->domain.id)
1766 domain_id_free(dom->domain.id);
1767
1768 kfree(dom);
1769}
1770
1771/*
1772 * Allocates a new protection domain usable for the dma_ops functions.
1773 * It also initializes the page table and the address allocator data
1774 * structures required for the dma_ops interface
1775 */
1776static struct dma_ops_domain *dma_ops_domain_alloc(void)
1777{
1778 struct dma_ops_domain *dma_dom;
1779
1780 dma_dom = kzalloc(sizeof(struct dma_ops_domain), GFP_KERNEL);
1781 if (!dma_dom)
1782 return NULL;
1783
1784 if (protection_domain_init(&dma_dom->domain))
1785 goto free_dma_dom;
1786
1787 dma_dom->domain.mode = PAGE_MODE_3_LEVEL;
1788 dma_dom->domain.pt_root = (void *)get_zeroed_page(GFP_KERNEL);
1789 dma_dom->domain.flags = PD_DMA_OPS_MASK;
1790 if (!dma_dom->domain.pt_root)
1791 goto free_dma_dom;
1792
1793 init_iova_domain(&dma_dom->iovad, PAGE_SIZE,
1794 IOVA_START_PFN, DMA_32BIT_PFN);
1795
1796 if (init_iova_flush_queue(&dma_dom->iovad, iova_domain_flush_tlb, NULL))
1797 goto free_dma_dom;
1798
1799 /* Initialize reserved ranges */
1800 copy_reserved_iova(&reserved_iova_ranges, &dma_dom->iovad);
1801
1802 add_domain_to_list(&dma_dom->domain);
1803
1804 return dma_dom;
1805
1806free_dma_dom:
1807 dma_ops_domain_free(dma_dom);
1808
1809 return NULL;
1810}

1812/*
1813 * little helper function to check whether a given protection domain is a
1814 * dma_ops domain
1815 */
1816static bool dma_ops_domain(struct protection_domain *domain)
1817{
1818 return domain->flags & PD_DMA_OPS_MASK;
1819}
1820
1821static void set_dte_entry(u16 devid, struct protection_domain *domain, bool ats)
1822{
1823 u64 pte_root = 0;
1824 u64 flags = 0;
1825
1826 if (domain->mode != PAGE_MODE_NONE)
1827 pte_root = iommu_virt_to_phys(domain->pt_root);
1828
1829 pte_root |= (domain->mode & DEV_ENTRY_MODE_MASK)
1830 << DEV_ENTRY_MODE_SHIFT;
1831 pte_root |= DTE_FLAG_IR | DTE_FLAG_IW | DTE_FLAG_V | DTE_FLAG_TV;
1832
1833 flags = amd_iommu_dev_table[devid].data[1];
1834
1835 if (ats)
1836 flags |= DTE_FLAG_IOTLB;
1837
1838 if (domain->flags & PD_IOMMUV2_MASK) {
1839 u64 gcr3 = iommu_virt_to_phys(domain->gcr3_tbl);
1840 u64 glx = domain->glx;
1841 u64 tmp;
1842
1843 pte_root |= DTE_FLAG_GV;
1844 pte_root |= (glx & DTE_GLX_MASK) << DTE_GLX_SHIFT;
1845
1846 /* First mask out possible old values for GCR3 table */
1847 tmp = DTE_GCR3_VAL_B(~0ULL) << DTE_GCR3_SHIFT_B;
1848 flags &= ~tmp;
1849
1850 tmp = DTE_GCR3_VAL_C(~0ULL) << DTE_GCR3_SHIFT_C;
1851 flags &= ~tmp;
1852
1853 /* Encode GCR3 table into DTE */
1854 tmp = DTE_GCR3_VAL_A(gcr3) << DTE_GCR3_SHIFT_A;
1855 pte_root |= tmp;
1856
1857 tmp = DTE_GCR3_VAL_B(gcr3) << DTE_GCR3_SHIFT_B;
1858 flags |= tmp;
1859
1860 tmp = DTE_GCR3_VAL_C(gcr3) << DTE_GCR3_SHIFT_C;
1861 flags |= tmp;
1862 }
1863
1864 flags &= ~DEV_DOMID_MASK;
1865 flags |= domain->id;
1866
1867 amd_iommu_dev_table[devid].data[1] = flags;
1868 amd_iommu_dev_table[devid].data[0] = pte_root;
1869}
1870
1871static void clear_dte_entry(u16 devid)
1872{
1873 /* remove entry from the device table seen by the hardware */
1874 amd_iommu_dev_table[devid].data[0] = DTE_FLAG_V | DTE_FLAG_TV;
1875 amd_iommu_dev_table[devid].data[1] &= DTE_FLAG_MASK;
1876
1877 amd_iommu_apply_erratum_63(devid);
1878}
1879
1880static void do_attach(struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data,
1881 struct protection_domain *domain)
1882{
1883 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
1884 u16 alias;
1885 bool ats;
1886
1887 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[dev_data->devid];
1888 alias = dev_data->alias;
1889 ats = dev_data->ats.enabled;
1890
1891 /* Update data structures */
1892 dev_data->domain = domain;
1893 list_add(&dev_data->list, &domain->dev_list);
1894
1895 /* Do reference counting */
1896 domain->dev_iommu[iommu->index] += 1;
1897 domain->dev_cnt += 1;
1898
1899 /* Update device table */
1900 set_dte_entry(dev_data->devid, domain, ats);
1901 if (alias != dev_data->devid)
1902 set_dte_entry(alias, domain, ats);
1903
1904 device_flush_dte(dev_data);
1905}
1906
1907static void do_detach(struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data)
1908{
1909 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
1910 u16 alias;
1911
1912 /*
1913 * First check if the device is still attached. It might already
1914 * be detached from its domain because the generic
1915 * iommu_detach_group code detached it and we try again here in
1916 * our alias handling.
1917 */
1918 if (!dev_data->domain)
1919 return;
1920
1921 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[dev_data->devid];
1922 alias = dev_data->alias;
1923
1924 /* decrease reference counters */
1925 dev_data->domain->dev_iommu[iommu->index] -= 1;
1926 dev_data->domain->dev_cnt -= 1;
1927
1928 /* Update data structures */
1929 dev_data->domain = NULL;
1930 list_del(&dev_data->list);
1931 clear_dte_entry(dev_data->devid);
1932 if (alias != dev_data->devid)
1933 clear_dte_entry(alias);
1934
1935 /* Flush the DTE entry */
1936 device_flush_dte(dev_data);
1937}
1938
1939/*
1940 * If a device is not yet associated with a domain, this function does
1941 * assigns it visible for the hardware
1942 */
1943static int __attach_device(struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data,
1944 struct protection_domain *domain)
1945{
1946 int ret;
1947
1948 /*
1949 * Must be called with IRQs disabled. Warn here to detect early
1950 * when its not.
1951 */
1952 WARN_ON(!irqs_disabled());
1953
1954 /* lock domain */
1955 spin_lock(&domain->lock);
1956
1957 ret = -EBUSY;
1958 if (dev_data->domain != NULL)
1959 goto out_unlock;
1960
1961 /* Attach alias group root */
1962 do_attach(dev_data, domain);
1963
1964 ret = 0;
1965
1966out_unlock:
1967
1968 /* ready */
1969 spin_unlock(&domain->lock);
1970
1971 return ret;
1972}

1975static void pdev_iommuv2_disable(struct pci_dev *pdev)
1976{
1977 pci_disable_ats(pdev);
1978 pci_disable_pri(pdev);
1979 pci_disable_pasid(pdev);
1980}

1982/* FIXME: Change generic reset-function to do the same */
1983static int pri_reset_while_enabled(struct pci_dev *pdev)
1984{
1985 u16 control;
1986 int pos;
1987
1988 pos = pci_find_ext_capability(pdev, PCI_EXT_CAP_ID_PRI);
1989 if (!pos)
1990 return -EINVAL;
1991
1992 pci_read_config_word(pdev, pos + PCI_PRI_CTRL, &control);
1993 control |= PCI_PRI_CTRL_RESET;
1994 pci_write_config_word(pdev, pos + PCI_PRI_CTRL, control);
1995
1996 return 0;
1997}
1998
1999static int pdev_iommuv2_enable(struct pci_dev *pdev)
2000{
2001 bool reset_enable;
2002 int reqs, ret;
2003
2004 /* FIXME: Hardcode number of outstanding requests for now */
2005 reqs = 32;
2006 if (pdev_pri_erratum(pdev, AMD_PRI_DEV_ERRATUM_LIMIT_REQ_ONE))
2007 reqs = 1;
2008 reset_enable = pdev_pri_erratum(pdev, AMD_PRI_DEV_ERRATUM_ENABLE_RESET);
2009
2010 /* Only allow access to user-accessible pages */
2011 ret = pci_enable_pasid(pdev, 0);
2012 if (ret)
2013 goto out_err;
2014
2015 /* First reset the PRI state of the device */
2016 ret = pci_reset_pri(pdev);
2017 if (ret)
2018 goto out_err;
2019
2020 /* Enable PRI */
2021 ret = pci_enable_pri(pdev, reqs);
2022 if (ret)
2023 goto out_err;
2024
2025 if (reset_enable) {
2026 ret = pri_reset_while_enabled(pdev);
2027 if (ret)
2028 goto out_err;
2029 }
2030
2031 ret = pci_enable_ats(pdev, PAGE_SHIFT);
2032 if (ret)
2033 goto out_err;
2034
2035 return 0;
2036
2037out_err:
2038 pci_disable_pri(pdev);
2039 pci_disable_pasid(pdev);
2040
2041 return ret;
2042}
2043
2044/* FIXME: Move this to PCI code */
2045#define PCI_PRI_TLP_OFF (1 << 15)
2046
2047static bool pci_pri_tlp_required(struct pci_dev *pdev)
2048{
2049 u16 status;
2050 int pos;
2051
2052 pos = pci_find_ext_capability(pdev, PCI_EXT_CAP_ID_PRI);
2053 if (!pos)
2054 return false;
2055
2056 pci_read_config_word(pdev, pos + PCI_PRI_STATUS, &status);
2057
2058 return (status & PCI_PRI_TLP_OFF) ? true : false;
2059}
2060
2061/*
2062 * If a device is not yet associated with a domain, this function
2063 * assigns it visible for the hardware
2064 */
2065static int attach_device(struct device *dev,
2066 struct protection_domain *domain)
2067{
2068 struct pci_dev *pdev;
2069 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data;
2070 unsigned long flags;
2071 int ret;
2072
2073 dev_data = get_dev_data(dev);
2074
2075 if (!dev_is_pci(dev))
2076 goto skip_ats_check;
2077
2078 pdev = to_pci_dev(dev);
2079 if (domain->flags & PD_IOMMUV2_MASK) {
2080 if (!dev_data->passthrough)
2081 return -EINVAL;
2082
2083 if (dev_data->iommu_v2) {
2084 if (pdev_iommuv2_enable(pdev) != 0)
2085 return -EINVAL;
2086
2087 dev_data->ats.enabled = true;
2088 dev_data->ats.qdep = pci_ats_queue_depth(pdev);
2089 dev_data->pri_tlp = pci_pri_tlp_required(pdev);
2090 }
2091 } else if (amd_iommu_iotlb_sup &&
2092 pci_enable_ats(pdev, PAGE_SHIFT) == 0) {
2093 dev_data->ats.enabled = true;
2094 dev_data->ats.qdep = pci_ats_queue_depth(pdev);
2095 }
2096
2097skip_ats_check:
2098 write_lock_irqsave(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
2099 ret = __attach_device(dev_data, domain);
2100 write_unlock_irqrestore(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
2101
2102 /*
2103 * We might boot into a crash-kernel here. The crashed kernel
2104 * left the caches in the IOMMU dirty. So we have to flush
2105 * here to evict all dirty stuff.
2106 */
2107 domain_flush_tlb_pde(domain);
2108
2109 return ret;
2110}

2112/*
2113 * Removes a device from a protection domain (unlocked)
2114 */
2115static void __detach_device(struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data)
2116{
2117 struct protection_domain *domain;
2118
2119 /*
2120 * Must be called with IRQs disabled. Warn here to detect early
2121 * when its not.
2122 */
2123 WARN_ON(!irqs_disabled());
2124
2125 if (WARN_ON(!dev_data->domain))
2126 return;
2127
2128 domain = dev_data->domain;
2129
2130 spin_lock(&domain->lock);
2131
2132 do_detach(dev_data);
2133
2134 spin_unlock(&domain->lock);
2135}
2136
2137/*
2138 * Removes a device from a protection domain (with devtable_lock held)
2139 */
2140static void detach_device(struct device *dev)
2141{
2142 struct protection_domain *domain;
2143 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data;
2144 unsigned long flags;
2145
2146 dev_data = get_dev_data(dev);
2147 domain = dev_data->domain;
2148
2149 /* lock device table */
2150 write_lock_irqsave(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
2151 __detach_device(dev_data);
2152 write_unlock_irqrestore(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
2153
2154 if (!dev_is_pci(dev))
2155 return;
2156
2157 if (domain->flags & PD_IOMMUV2_MASK && dev_data->iommu_v2)
2158 pdev_iommuv2_disable(to_pci_dev(dev));
2159 else if (dev_data->ats.enabled)
2160 pci_disable_ats(to_pci_dev(dev));
2161
2162 dev_data->ats.enabled = false;
2163}

2165static int amd_iommu_add_device(struct device *dev)
2166{
2167 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data;
2168 struct iommu_domain *domain;
2169 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
2170 int ret, devid;
2171
2172 if (!check_device(dev) || get_dev_data(dev))
2173 return 0;
2174
2175 devid = get_device_id(dev);
2176 if (devid < 0)
2177 return devid;
2178
2179 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
2180
2181 ret = iommu_init_device(dev);
2182 if (ret) {

2190 }

2199

2201 domain = iommu_get_domain_for_dev(dev);

2203 dev_data->passthrough = true;

2207out:

2211}

2304static int dir2prot(enum dma_data_direction direction)
2305{
2306 if (direction == DMA_TO_DEVICE)
2307 return IOMMU_PROT_IR;
2308 else if (direction == DMA_FROM_DEVICE)
2309 return IOMMU_PROT_IW;
2310 else if (direction == DMA_BIDIRECTIONAL)
2311 return IOMMU_PROT_IW | IOMMU_PROT_IR;
2312 else
2313 return 0;
2314}

2316/*
2317 * This function contains common code for mapping of a physically
2318 * contiguous memory region into DMA address space. It is used by all
2319 * mapping functions provided with this IOMMU driver.
2320 * Must be called with the domain lock held.
2321 */
2322static dma_addr_t __map_single(struct device *dev,
2323 struct dma_ops_domain *dma_dom,
2324 phys_addr_t paddr,
2325 size_t size,
2326 enum dma_data_direction direction,
2327 u64 dma_mask)
2328{
2329 dma_addr_t offset = paddr & ~PAGE_MASK;
2330 dma_addr_t address, start, ret;
2331 unsigned int pages;
2332 int prot = 0;
2333 int i;
2334
2335 pages = iommu_num_pages(paddr, size, PAGE_SIZE);
2336 paddr &= PAGE_MASK;
2337
2338 address = dma_ops_alloc_iova(dev, dma_dom, pages, dma_mask);
2339 if (address == AMD_IOMMU_MAPPING_ERROR)
2340 goto out;
2341
2342 prot = dir2prot(direction);
2343
2344 start = address;
2345 for (i = 0; i < pages; ++i) {
2346 ret = iommu_map_page(&dma_dom->domain, start, paddr,
2347 PAGE_SIZE, prot, GFP_ATOMIC);
2348 if (ret)
2349 goto out_unmap;
2350
2351 paddr += PAGE_SIZE;
2352 start += PAGE_SIZE;
2353 }
2354 address += offset;
2355
2356 if (unlikely(amd_iommu_np_cache)) {
2357 domain_flush_pages(&dma_dom->domain, address, size);
2358 domain_flush_complete(&dma_dom->domain);
2359 }
2360
2361out:
2362 return address;
2363
2364out_unmap:
2365
2366 for (--i; i >= 0; --i) {
2367 start -= PAGE_SIZE;
2368 iommu_unmap_page(&dma_dom->domain, start, PAGE_SIZE);
2369 }
2370
2371 domain_flush_tlb(&dma_dom->domain);
2372 domain_flush_complete(&dma_dom->domain);
2373
2374 dma_ops_free_iova(dma_dom, address, pages);
2375
2376 return AMD_IOMMU_MAPPING_ERROR;
2377}
2378
2379/*
2380 * Does the reverse of the __map_single function. Must be called with
2381 * the domain lock held too
2382 */
2383static void __unmap_single(struct dma_ops_domain *dma_dom,
2384 dma_addr_t dma_addr,
2385 size_t size,
2386 int dir)
2387{
2388 dma_addr_t flush_addr;
2389 dma_addr_t i, start;
2390 unsigned int pages;
2391
2392 flush_addr = dma_addr;
2393 pages = iommu_num_pages(dma_addr, size, PAGE_SIZE);
2394 dma_addr &= PAGE_MASK;
2395 start = dma_addr;
2396
2397 for (i = 0; i < pages; ++i) {
2398 iommu_unmap_page(&dma_dom->domain, start, PAGE_SIZE);
2399 start += PAGE_SIZE;
2400 }
2401
2402 if (amd_iommu_unmap_flush) {
2403 dma_ops_free_iova(dma_dom, dma_addr, pages);
2404 domain_flush_tlb(&dma_dom->domain);
2405 domain_flush_complete(&dma_dom->domain);
2406 } else {
2407 pages = __roundup_pow_of_two(pages);
2408 queue_iova(&dma_dom->iovad, dma_addr >> PAGE_SHIFT, pages, 0);
2409 }
2410}

2412/*
2413 * The exported map_single function for dma_ops.
2414 */
2415static dma_addr_t map_page(struct device *dev, struct page *page,
2416 unsigned long offset, size_t size,
2417 enum dma_data_direction dir,
2418 unsigned long attrs)
2419{
2420 phys_addr_t paddr = page_to_phys(page) + offset;

2422 struct dma_ops_domain *dma_dom;
2423 u64 dma_mask;
2424

2426 if (PTR_ERR(domain) == -EINVAL)
2427 return (dma_addr_t)paddr;
2428 else if (IS_ERR(domain))
2429 return AMD_IOMMU_MAPPING_ERROR;
2430
2431 dma_mask = *dev->dma_mask;
2432 dma_dom = to_dma_ops_domain(domain);
2433
2434 return __map_single(dev, dma_dom, paddr, size, dir, dma_mask);

2455static int sg_num_pages(struct device *dev,
2456 struct scatterlist *sglist,
2457 int nelems)
2458{
2459 unsigned long mask, boundary_size;
2460 struct scatterlist *s;
2461 int i, npages = 0;
2462
2463 mask = dma_get_seg_boundary(dev);
2464 boundary_size = mask + 1 ? ALIGN(mask + 1, PAGE_SIZE) >> PAGE_SHIFT :
2465 1UL << (BITS_PER_LONG - PAGE_SHIFT);
2466
2467 for_each_sg(sglist, s, nelems, i) {
2468 int p, n;
2469
2470 s->dma_address = npages << PAGE_SHIFT;
2471 p = npages % boundary_size;
2472 n = iommu_num_pages(sg_phys(s), s->length, PAGE_SIZE);
2473 if (p + n > boundary_size)
2474 npages += boundary_size - p;
2475 npages += n;
2476 }
2477
2478 return npages;
2479}
2480
2481/*
2482 * The exported map_sg function for dma_ops (handles scatter-gather
2483 * lists).
2484 */
2485static int map_sg(struct device *dev, struct scatterlist *sglist,
2486 int nelems, enum dma_data_direction direction,
2487 unsigned long attrs)
2488{
2489 int mapped_pages = 0, npages = 0, prot = 0, i;
2490 struct protection_domain *domain;
2491 struct dma_ops_domain *dma_dom;
2492 struct scatterlist *s;
2493 unsigned long address;
2494 u64 dma_mask;
2495
2496 domain = get_domain(dev);
2497 if (IS_ERR(domain))
2498 return 0;
2499
2500 dma_dom = to_dma_ops_domain(domain);
2501 dma_mask = *dev->dma_mask;
2502
2503 npages = sg_num_pages(dev, sglist, nelems);
2504
2505 address = dma_ops_alloc_iova(dev, dma_dom, npages, dma_mask);
2506 if (address == AMD_IOMMU_MAPPING_ERROR)
2507 goto out_err;
2508
2509 prot = dir2prot(direction);
2510
2511 /* Map all sg entries */
2512 for_each_sg(sglist, s, nelems, i) {
2513 int j, pages = iommu_num_pages(sg_phys(s), s->length, PAGE_SIZE);
2514
2515 for (j = 0; j < pages; ++j) {
2516 unsigned long bus_addr, phys_addr;
2517 int ret;
2518
2519 bus_addr = address + s->dma_address + (j << PAGE_SHIFT);
2520 phys_addr = (sg_phys(s) & PAGE_MASK) + (j << PAGE_SHIFT);
2521 ret = iommu_map_page(domain, bus_addr, phys_addr, PAGE_SIZE, prot, GFP_ATOMIC);
2522 if (ret)
2523 goto out_unmap;
2524
2525 mapped_pages += 1;
2526 }
2527 }
2528
2529 /* Everything is mapped - write the right values into s->dma_address */
2530 for_each_sg(sglist, s, nelems, i) {
2531 s->dma_address += address + s->offset;
2532 s->dma_length = s->length;
2533 }
2534
2535 return nelems;
2536
2537out_unmap:
2538 pr_err("%s: IOMMU mapping error in map_sg (io-pages: %d)\n",
2539 dev_name(dev), npages);
2540
2541 for_each_sg(sglist, s, nelems, i) {
2542 int j, pages = iommu_num_pages(sg_phys(s), s->length, PAGE_SIZE);
2543
2544 for (j = 0; j < pages; ++j) {
2545 unsigned long bus_addr;
2546
2547 bus_addr = address + s->dma_address + (j << PAGE_SHIFT);
2548 iommu_unmap_page(domain, bus_addr, PAGE_SIZE);
2549
2550 if (--mapped_pages)
2551 goto out_free_iova;
2552 }
2553 }
2554
2555out_free_iova:
2556 free_iova_fast(&dma_dom->iovad, address, npages);
2557
2558out_err:
2559 return 0;
2560}

2562/*
2563 * The exported map_sg function for dma_ops (handles scatter-gather
2564 * lists).
2565 */
2566static void unmap_sg(struct device *dev, struct scatterlist *sglist,
2567 int nelems, enum dma_data_direction dir,
2568 unsigned long attrs)
2569{
2570 struct protection_domain *domain;
2571 struct dma_ops_domain *dma_dom;
2572 unsigned long startaddr;
2573 int npages = 2;
2574
2575 domain = get_domain(dev);
2576 if (IS_ERR(domain))
2577 return;
2578
2579 startaddr = sg_dma_address(sglist) & PAGE_MASK;
2580 dma_dom = to_dma_ops_domain(domain);
2581 npages = sg_num_pages(dev, sglist, nelems);
2582
2583 __unmap_single(dma_dom, startaddr, npages << PAGE_SHIFT, dir);
2584}

2586/*
2587 * The exported alloc_coherent function for dma_ops.
2588 */
2589static void *alloc_coherent(struct device *dev, size_t size,
2590 dma_addr_t *dma_addr, gfp_t flag,
2591 unsigned long attrs)
2592{
2593 u64 dma_mask = dev->coherent_dma_mask;
2594 struct protection_domain *domain;
2595 struct dma_ops_domain *dma_dom;
2596 struct page *page;
2597
2598 domain = get_domain(dev);
2599 if (PTR_ERR(domain) == -EINVAL) {
2600 page = alloc_pages(flag, get_order(size));
2601 *dma_addr = page_to_phys(page);
2602 return page_address(page);
2603 } else if (IS_ERR(domain))
2604 return NULL;
2605
2606 dma_dom = to_dma_ops_domain(domain);
2607 size = PAGE_ALIGN(size);
2608 dma_mask = dev->coherent_dma_mask;
2609 flag &= ~(__GFP_DMA | __GFP_HIGHMEM | __GFP_DMA32);
2610 flag |= __GFP_ZERO;
2611
2612 page = alloc_pages(flag | __GFP_NOWARN, get_order(size));
2613 if (!page) {
2614 if (!gfpflags_allow_blocking(flag))
2615 return NULL;
2616
2617 page = dma_alloc_from_contiguous(dev, size >> PAGE_SHIFT,
2618 get_order(size), flag);
2619 if (!page)
2620 return NULL;
2621 }
2622
2623 if (!dma_mask)
2624 dma_mask = *dev->dma_mask;
2625
2626 *dma_addr = __map_single(dev, dma_dom, page_to_phys(page),
2627 size, DMA_BIDIRECTIONAL, dma_mask);
2628
2629 if (*dma_addr == AMD_IOMMU_MAPPING_ERROR)
2630 goto out_free;
2631
2632 return page_address(page);
2633
2634out_free:
2635
2636 if (!dma_release_from_contiguous(dev, page, size >> PAGE_SHIFT))
2637 __free_pages(page, get_order(size));
2638
2639 return NULL;
2640}

2642/*
2643 * The exported free_coherent function for dma_ops.
2644 */
2645static void free_coherent(struct device *dev, size_t size,
2646 void *virt_addr, dma_addr_t dma_addr,
2647 unsigned long attrs)
2648{
2649 struct protection_domain *domain;
2650 struct dma_ops_domain *dma_dom;
2651 struct page *page;
2652
2653 page = virt_to_page(virt_addr);
2654 size = PAGE_ALIGN(size);
2655
2656 domain = get_domain(dev);
2657 if (IS_ERR(domain))
2658 goto free_mem;
2659
2660 dma_dom = to_dma_ops_domain(domain);
2661
2662 __unmap_single(dma_dom, dma_addr, size, DMA_BIDIRECTIONAL);
2663
2664free_mem:
2665 if (!dma_release_from_contiguous(dev, page, size >> PAGE_SHIFT))
2666 __free_pages(page, get_order(size));
2667}

2696static int init_reserved_iova_ranges(void)
2697{
2698 struct pci_dev *pdev = NULL;
2699 struct iova *val;
2700
2701 init_iova_domain(&reserved_iova_ranges, PAGE_SIZE,
2702 IOVA_START_PFN, DMA_32BIT_PFN);
2703
2704 lockdep_set_class(&reserved_iova_ranges.iova_rbtree_lock,
2705 &reserved_rbtree_key);
2706
2707 /* MSI memory range */
2708 val = reserve_iova(&reserved_iova_ranges,
2709 IOVA_PFN(MSI_RANGE_START), IOVA_PFN(MSI_RANGE_END));
2710 if (!val) {
2711 pr_err("Reserving MSI range failed\n");
2712 return -ENOMEM;
2713 }
2714
2715 /* HT memory range */
2716 val = reserve_iova(&reserved_iova_ranges,
2717 IOVA_PFN(HT_RANGE_START), IOVA_PFN(HT_RANGE_END));
2718 if (!val) {
2719 pr_err("Reserving HT range failed\n");
2720 return -ENOMEM;
2721 }
2722
2723 /*
2724 * Memory used for PCI resources
2725 * FIXME: Check whether we can reserve the PCI-hole completly
2726 */
2727 for_each_pci_dev(pdev) {
2728 int i;
2729
2730 for (i = 0; i < PCI_NUM_RESOURCES; ++i) {
2731 struct resource *r = &pdev->resource[i];
2732
2733 if (!(r->flags & IORESOURCE_MEM))
2734 continue;
2735
2736 val = reserve_iova(&reserved_iova_ranges,
2737 IOVA_PFN(r->start),
2738 IOVA_PFN(r->end));
2739 if (!val) {
2740 pr_err("Reserve pci-resource range failed\n");
2741 return -ENOMEM;
2742 }
2743 }
2744 }
2745
2746 return 0;
2747}

2749int __init amd_iommu_init_api(void)
2750{
2751 int ret, err = 0;
2752
2753 ret = iova_cache_get();
2754 if (ret)
2755 return ret;
2756
2757 ret = init_reserved_iova_ranges();
2758 if (ret)
2759 return ret;
2760
2761 err = bus_set_iommu(&pci_bus_type, &amd_iommu_ops);
2762 if (err)
2763 return err;
2764#ifdef CONFIG_ARM_AMBA
2765 err = bus_set_iommu(&amba_bustype, &amd_iommu_ops);
2766 if (err)
2767 return err;
2768#endif
2769 err = bus_set_iommu(&platform_bus_type, &amd_iommu_ops);
2770 if (err)
2771 return err;
2772
2773 return 0;
2774}
2775
2776int __init amd_iommu_init_dma_ops(void)
2777{
2778 swiotlb = (iommu_pass_through || sme_me_mask) ? 1 : 0;
2779 iommu_detected = 1;
2780
2781 /*
2782 * In case we don't initialize SWIOTLB (actually the common case
2783 * when AMD IOMMU is enabled and SME is not active), make sure there
2784 * are global dma_ops set as a fall-back for devices not handled by
2785 * this driver (for example non-PCI devices). When SME is active,
2786 * make sure that swiotlb variable remains set so the global dma_ops
2787 * continue to be SWIOTLB.
2788 */
2789 if (!swiotlb)
2790 dma_ops = &nommu_dma_ops;
2791
2792 if (amd_iommu_unmap_flush)
2793 pr_info("AMD-Vi: IO/TLB flush on unmap enabled\n");
2794 else
2795 pr_info("AMD-Vi: Lazy IO/TLB flushing enabled\n");
2796
2797 return 0;
2798
2799}

2811static void cleanup_domain(struct protection_domain *domain)
2812{
2813 struct iommu_dev_data *entry;
2814 unsigned long flags;
2815
2816 write_lock_irqsave(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
2817
2818 while (!list_empty(&domain->dev_list)) {
2819 entry = list_first_entry(&domain->dev_list,
2820 struct iommu_dev_data, list);
2821 __detach_device(entry);
2822 }
2823
2824 write_unlock_irqrestore(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
2825}

2828{

2830 return;
2831
2832 del_domain_from_list(domain);
2833
2834 if (domain->id)
2835 domain_id_free(domain->id);
2836
2837 kfree(domain);
2838}

2873static struct iommu_domain *amd_iommu_domain_alloc(unsigned type)
2874{
2875 struct protection_domain *pdomain;
2876 struct dma_ops_domain *dma_domain;
2877
2878 switch (type) {
2879 case IOMMU_DOMAIN_UNMANAGED:
2880 pdomain = protection_domain_alloc();
2881 if (!pdomain)
2882 return NULL;
2883
2884 pdomain->mode = PAGE_MODE_3_LEVEL;
2885 pdomain->pt_root = (void *)get_zeroed_page(GFP_KERNEL);
2886 if (!pdomain->pt_root) {
2887 protection_domain_free(pdomain);
2888 return NULL;
2889 }
2890
2891 pdomain->domain.geometry.aperture_start = 0;
2892 pdomain->domain.geometry.aperture_end = ~0ULL;
2893 pdomain->domain.geometry.force_aperture = true;
2894
2895 break;
2896 case IOMMU_DOMAIN_DMA:
2897 dma_domain = dma_ops_domain_alloc();
2898 if (!dma_domain) {
2899 pr_err("AMD-Vi: Failed to allocate\n");
2900 return NULL;
2901 }
2902 pdomain = &dma_domain->domain;
2903 break;
2904 case IOMMU_DOMAIN_IDENTITY:
2905 pdomain = protection_domain_alloc();
2906 if (!pdomain)
2907 return NULL;
2908
2909 pdomain->mode = PAGE_MODE_NONE;
2910 break;
2911 default:
2912 return NULL;
2913 }
2914
2915 return &pdomain->domain;
2916}
2917
2918static void amd_iommu_domain_free(struct iommu_domain *dom)
2919{
2920 struct protection_domain *domain;
2921 struct dma_ops_domain *dma_dom;
2922
2923 domain = to_pdomain(dom);
2924
2925 if (domain->dev_cnt > 0)
2926 cleanup_domain(domain);
2927
2928 BUG_ON(domain->dev_cnt != 0);
2929
2930 if (!dom)
2931 return;
2932
2933 switch (dom->type) {
2934 case IOMMU_DOMAIN_DMA:
2935 /* Now release the domain */
2936 dma_dom = to_dma_ops_domain(domain);
2937 dma_ops_domain_free(dma_dom);
2938 break;
2939 default:
2940 if (domain->mode != PAGE_MODE_NONE)
2941 free_pagetable(domain);
2942
2943 if (domain->flags & PD_IOMMUV2_MASK)
2944 free_gcr3_table(domain);
2945
2946 protection_domain_free(domain);
2947 break;
2948 }
2949}

3017static int amd_iommu_map(struct iommu_domain *dom, unsigned long iova,
3018 phys_addr_t paddr, size_t page_size, int iommu_prot)
3019{
3020 struct protection_domain *domain = to_pdomain(dom);
3021 int prot = 0;
3022 int ret;
3023
3024 if (domain->mode == PAGE_MODE_NONE)
3025 return -EINVAL;
3026
3027 if (iommu_prot & IOMMU_READ)
3028 prot |= IOMMU_PROT_IR;
3029 if (iommu_prot & IOMMU_WRITE)
3030 prot |= IOMMU_PROT_IW;
3031
3032 mutex_lock(&domain->api_lock);
3033 ret = iommu_map_page(domain, iova, paddr, page_size, prot, GFP_KERNEL);
3034 mutex_unlock(&domain->api_lock);
3035
3036 return ret;
3037}

3039static size_t amd_iommu_unmap(struct iommu_domain *dom, unsigned long iova,
3040 size_t page_size)
3041{

3043 size_t unmap_size;
3044

3046 return -EINVAL;
3047
3048 mutex_lock(&domain->api_lock);
3049 unmap_size = iommu_unmap_page(domain, iova, page_size);
3050 mutex_unlock(&domain->api_lock);
3051
3052 domain_flush_tlb_pde(domain);

3058static phys_addr_t amd_iommu_iova_to_phys(struct iommu_domain *dom,
3059 dma_addr_t iova)
3060{
3061 struct protection_domain *domain = to_pdomain(dom);
3062 unsigned long offset_mask, pte_pgsize;
3063 u64 *pte, __pte;
3064
3065 if (domain->mode == PAGE_MODE_NONE)
3066 return iova;
3067
3068 pte = fetch_pte(domain, iova, &pte_pgsize);
3069
3070 if (!pte || !IOMMU_PTE_PRESENT(*pte))
3071 return 0;
3072
3073 offset_mask = pte_pgsize - 1;
3074 __pte = *pte & PM_ADDR_MASK;
3075
3076 return (__pte & ~offset_mask) | (iova & offset_mask);
3077}

3093static void amd_iommu_get_resv_regions(struct device *dev,
3094 struct list_head *head)
3095{
3096 struct iommu_resv_region *region;
3097 struct unity_map_entry *entry;
3098 int devid;
3099
3100 devid = get_device_id(dev);
3101 if (devid < 0)
3102 return;
3103
3104 list_for_each_entry(entry, &amd_iommu_unity_map, list) {
3105 size_t length;
3106 int prot = 0;
3107
3108 if (devid < entry->devid_start || devid > entry->devid_end)
3109 continue;
3110
3111 length = entry->address_end - entry->address_start;
3112 if (entry->prot & IOMMU_PROT_IR)
3113 prot |= IOMMU_READ;
3114 if (entry->prot & IOMMU_PROT_IW)
3115 prot |= IOMMU_WRITE;
3116
3117 region = iommu_alloc_resv_region(entry->address_start,
3118 length, prot,
3119 IOMMU_RESV_DIRECT);
3120 if (!region) {
3121 pr_err("Out of memory allocating dm-regions for %s\n",
3122 dev_name(dev));
3123 return;
3124 }
3125 list_add_tail(&region->list, head);
3126 }
3127
3128 region = iommu_alloc_resv_region(MSI_RANGE_START,
3129 MSI_RANGE_END - MSI_RANGE_START + 1,
3130 0, IOMMU_RESV_MSI);
3131 if (!region)
3132 return;
3133 list_add_tail(&region->list, head);
3134
3135 region = iommu_alloc_resv_region(HT_RANGE_START,
3136 HT_RANGE_END - HT_RANGE_START + 1,
3137 0, IOMMU_RESV_RESERVED);
3138 if (!region)
3139 return;
3140 list_add_tail(&region->list, head);
3141}

3215void amd_iommu_domain_direct_map(struct iommu_domain *dom)
3216{

3218 unsigned long flags;
3219

3221

3223 domain->mode = PAGE_MODE_NONE;
3224 domain->updated = true;
3225

3227 update_domain(domain);

3236int amd_iommu_domain_enable_v2(struct iommu_domain *dom, int pasids)
3237{
3238 struct protection_domain *domain = to_pdomain(dom);
3239 unsigned long flags;
3240 int levels, ret;
3241
3242 if (pasids <= 0 || pasids > (PASID_MASK + 1))
3243 return -EINVAL;
3244
3245 /* Number of GCR3 table levels required */
3246 for (levels = 0; (pasids - 1) & ~0x1ff; pasids >>= 9)
3247 levels += 1;
3248
3249 if (levels > amd_iommu_max_glx_val)
3250 return -EINVAL;
3251
3252 spin_lock_irqsave(&domain->lock, flags);
3253
3254 /*
3255 * Save us all sanity checks whether devices already in the
3256 * domain support IOMMUv2. Just force that the domain has no
3257 * devices attached when it is switched into IOMMUv2 mode.
3258 */
3259 ret = -EBUSY;
3260 if (domain->dev_cnt > 0 || domain->flags & PD_IOMMUV2_MASK)
3261 goto out;
3262
3263 ret = -ENOMEM;
3264 domain->gcr3_tbl = (void *)get_zeroed_page(GFP_ATOMIC);
3265 if (domain->gcr3_tbl == NULL)
3266 goto out;
3267
3268 domain->glx = levels;
3269 domain->flags |= PD_IOMMUV2_MASK;
3270 domain->updated = true;
3271
3272 update_domain(domain);
3273
3274 ret = 0;
3275
3276out:
3277 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&domain->lock, flags);
3278
3279 return ret;
3280}
3281EXPORT_SYMBOL(amd_iommu_domain_enable_v2);

3283static int __flush_pasid(struct protection_domain *domain, int pasid,
3284 u64 address, bool size)
3285{
3286 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data;
3287 struct iommu_cmd cmd;
3288 int i, ret;
3289
3290 if (!(domain->flags & PD_IOMMUV2_MASK))
3291 return -EINVAL;
3292
3293 build_inv_iommu_pasid(&cmd, domain->id, pasid, address, size);
3294
3295 /*
3296 * IOMMU TLB needs to be flushed before Device TLB to
3297 * prevent device TLB refill from IOMMU TLB
3298 */
3299 for (i = 0; i < amd_iommu_get_num_iommus(); ++i) {
3300 if (domain->dev_iommu[i] == 0)
3301 continue;
3302
3303 ret = iommu_queue_command(amd_iommus[i], &cmd);
3304 if (ret != 0)
3305 goto out;
3306 }
3307
3308 /* Wait until IOMMU TLB flushes are complete */
3309 domain_flush_complete(domain);
3310
3311 /* Now flush device TLBs */
3312 list_for_each_entry(dev_data, &domain->dev_list, list) {
3313 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
3314 int qdep;
3315
3316 /*
3317 There might be non-IOMMUv2 capable devices in an IOMMUv2
3318 * domain.
3319 */
3320 if (!dev_data->ats.enabled)
3321 continue;
3322
3323 qdep = dev_data->ats.qdep;
3324 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[dev_data->devid];
3325
3326 build_inv_iotlb_pasid(&cmd, dev_data->devid, pasid,
3327 qdep, address, size);
3328
3329 ret = iommu_queue_command(iommu, &cmd);
3330 if (ret != 0)
3331 goto out;
3332 }
3333
3334 /* Wait until all device TLBs are flushed */
3335 domain_flush_complete(domain);
3336
3337 ret = 0;
3338
3339out:
3340
3341 return ret;
3342}

3385static u64 *__get_gcr3_pte(u64 *root, int level, int pasid, bool alloc)
3386{
3387 int index;
3388 u64 *pte;
3389
3390 while (true) {
3391
3392 index = (pasid >> (9 * level)) & 0x1ff;
3393 pte = &root[index];
3394
3395 if (level == 0)
3396 break;
3397
3398 if (!(*pte & GCR3_VALID)) {
3399 if (!alloc)
3400 return NULL;
3401
3402 root = (void *)get_zeroed_page(GFP_ATOMIC);
3403 if (root == NULL)
3404 return NULL;
3405
3406 *pte = iommu_virt_to_phys(root) | GCR3_VALID;
3407 }
3408
3409 root = iommu_phys_to_virt(*pte & PAGE_MASK);
3410
3411 level -= 1;
3412 }
3413
3414 return pte;
3415}

3417static int __set_gcr3(struct protection_domain *domain, int pasid,
3418 unsigned long cr3)
3419{
3420 u64 *pte;
3421
3422 if (domain->mode != PAGE_MODE_NONE)
3423 return -EINVAL;
3424
3425 pte = __get_gcr3_pte(domain->gcr3_tbl, domain->glx, pasid, true);
3426 if (pte == NULL)
3427 return -ENOMEM;
3428
3429 *pte = (cr3 & PAGE_MASK) | GCR3_VALID;
3430
3431 return __amd_iommu_flush_tlb(domain, pasid);
3432}

3524int amd_iommu_device_info(struct pci_dev *pdev,
3525 struct amd_iommu_device_info *info)
3526{
3527 int max_pasids;
3528 int pos;
3529
3530 if (pdev == NULL || info == NULL)
3531 return -EINVAL;
3532
3533 if (!amd_iommu_v2_supported())
3534 return -EINVAL;
3535
3536 memset(info, 0, sizeof(*info));
3537
3538 pos = pci_find_ext_capability(pdev, PCI_EXT_CAP_ID_ATS);
3539 if (pos)
3540 info->flags |= AMD_IOMMU_DEVICE_FLAG_ATS_SUP;
3541
3542 pos = pci_find_ext_capability(pdev, PCI_EXT_CAP_ID_PRI);
3543 if (pos)
3544 info->flags |= AMD_IOMMU_DEVICE_FLAG_PRI_SUP;
3545
3546 pos = pci_find_ext_capability(pdev, PCI_EXT_CAP_ID_PASID);
3547 if (pos) {
3548 int features;
3549
3550 max_pasids = 1 << (9 * (amd_iommu_max_glx_val + 1));
3551 max_pasids = min(max_pasids, (1 << 20));
3552
3553 info->flags |= AMD_IOMMU_DEVICE_FLAG_PASID_SUP;
3554 info->max_pasids = min(pci_max_pasids(pdev), max_pasids);
3555
3556 features = pci_pasid_features(pdev);
3557 if (features & PCI_PASID_CAP_EXEC)
3558 info->flags |= AMD_IOMMU_DEVICE_FLAG_EXEC_SUP;
3559 if (features & PCI_PASID_CAP_PRIV)
3560 info->flags |= AMD_IOMMU_DEVICE_FLAG_PRIV_SUP;
3561 }
3562
3563 return 0;
3564}
3565EXPORT_SYMBOL(amd_iommu_device_info);

3576
3577static void set_dte_irq_entry(u16 devid, struct irq_remap_table *table)
3578{
3579 u64 dte;
3580
3581 dte = amd_iommu_dev_table[devid].data[2];
3582 dte &= ~DTE_IRQ_PHYS_ADDR_MASK;
3583 dte |= iommu_virt_to_phys(table->table);
3584 dte |= DTE_IRQ_REMAP_INTCTL;
3585 dte |= DTE_IRQ_TABLE_LEN;
3586 dte |= DTE_IRQ_REMAP_ENABLE;
3587
3588 amd_iommu_dev_table[devid].data[2] = dte;
3589}
3590
3591static struct irq_remap_table *get_irq_table(u16 devid, bool ioapic)
3592{
3593 struct irq_remap_table *table = NULL;
3594 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
3595 unsigned long flags;
3596 u16 alias;
3597
3598 write_lock_irqsave(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
3599
3600 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
3601 if (!iommu)
3602 goto out_unlock;
3603
3604 table = irq_lookup_table[devid];
3605 if (table)
3606 goto out_unlock;
3607
3608 alias = amd_iommu_alias_table[devid];
3609 table = irq_lookup_table[alias];
3610 if (table) {
3611 irq_lookup_table[devid] = table;
3612 set_dte_irq_entry(devid, table);
3613 iommu_flush_dte(iommu, devid);
3614 goto out;
3615 }
3616
3617 /* Nothing there yet, allocate new irq remapping table */
3618 table = kzalloc(sizeof(*table), GFP_ATOMIC);
3619 if (!table)
3620 goto out_unlock;
3621
3622 /* Initialize table spin-lock */
3623 spin_lock_init(&table->lock);
3624
3625 if (ioapic)
3626 /* Keep the first 32 indexes free for IOAPIC interrupts */
3627 table->min_index = 32;
3628
3629 table->table = kmem_cache_alloc(amd_iommu_irq_cache, GFP_ATOMIC);
3630 if (!table->table) {
3631 kfree(table);
3632 table = NULL;
3633 goto out_unlock;
3634 }
3635
3636 if (!AMD_IOMMU_GUEST_IR_GA(amd_iommu_guest_ir))
3637 memset(table->table, 0,
3638 MAX_IRQS_PER_TABLE * sizeof(u32));
3639 else
3640 memset(table->table, 0,
3641 (MAX_IRQS_PER_TABLE * (sizeof(u64) * 2)));
3642
3643 if (ioapic) {
3644 int i;
3645
3646 for (i = 0; i < 32; ++i)
3647 iommu->irte_ops->set_allocated(table, i);
3648 }
3649
3650 irq_lookup_table[devid] = table;
3651 set_dte_irq_entry(devid, table);
3652 iommu_flush_dte(iommu, devid);
3653 if (devid != alias) {
3654 irq_lookup_table[alias] = table;
3655 set_dte_irq_entry(alias, table);
3656 iommu_flush_dte(iommu, alias);
3657 }
3658
3659out:
3660 iommu_completion_wait(iommu);
3661
3662out_unlock:
3663 write_unlock_irqrestore(&amd_iommu_devtable_lock, flags);
3664
3665 return table;
3666}
3667
3668static int alloc_irq_index(u16 devid, int count)
3669{
3670 struct irq_remap_table *table;
3671 unsigned long flags;
3672 int index, c;
3673 struct amd_iommu *iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
3674
3675 if (!iommu)
3676 return -ENODEV;
3677
3678 table = get_irq_table(devid, false);
3679 if (!table)
3680 return -ENODEV;
3681
3682 spin_lock_irqsave(&table->lock, flags);
3683
3684 /* Scan table for free entries */
3685 for (c = 0, index = table->min_index;
3686 index < MAX_IRQS_PER_TABLE;
3687 ++index) {
3688 if (!iommu->irte_ops->is_allocated(table, index))
3689 c += 1;
3690 else
3691 c = 0;
3692
3693 if (c == count) {
3694 for (; c != 0; --c)
3695 iommu->irte_ops->set_allocated(table, index - c + 1);
3696
3697 index -= count - 1;
3698 goto out;
3699 }
3700 }
3701
3702 index = -ENOSPC;
3703
3704out:
3705 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&table->lock, flags);
3706
3707 return index;
3708}

3710static int modify_irte_ga(u16 devid, int index, struct irte_ga *irte,
3711 struct amd_ir_data *data)
3712{
3713 struct irq_remap_table *table;
3714 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
3715 unsigned long flags;
3716 struct irte_ga *entry;
3717
3718 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
3719 if (iommu == NULL)
3720 return -EINVAL;
3721
3722 table = get_irq_table(devid, false);
3723 if (!table)
3724 return -ENOMEM;
3725
3726 spin_lock_irqsave(&table->lock, flags);
3727
3728 entry = (struct irte_ga *)table->table;
3729 entry = &entry[index];
3730 entry->lo.fields_remap.valid = 0;
3731 entry->hi.val = irte->hi.val;
3732 entry->lo.val = irte->lo.val;
3733 entry->lo.fields_remap.valid = 1;
3734 if (data)
3735 data->ref = entry;
3736
3737 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&table->lock, flags);
3738
3739 iommu_flush_irt(iommu, devid);
3740 iommu_completion_wait(iommu);
3741
3742 return 0;
3743}

3745static int modify_irte(u16 devid, int index, union irte *irte)
3746{
3747 struct irq_remap_table *table;
3748 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
3749 unsigned long flags;
3750
3751 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
3752 if (iommu == NULL)
3753 return -EINVAL;
3754
3755 table = get_irq_table(devid, false);
3756 if (!table)
3757 return -ENOMEM;
3758
3759 spin_lock_irqsave(&table->lock, flags);
3760 table->table[index] = irte->val;
3761 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&table->lock, flags);
3762
3763 iommu_flush_irt(iommu, devid);
3764 iommu_completion_wait(iommu);
3765
3766 return 0;
3767}

3769static void free_irte(u16 devid, int index)
3770{
3771 struct irq_remap_table *table;
3772 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
3773 unsigned long flags;
3774
3775 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
3776 if (iommu == NULL)
3777 return;
3778
3779 table = get_irq_table(devid, false);
3780 if (!table)
3781 return;
3782
3783 spin_lock_irqsave(&table->lock, flags);
3784 iommu->irte_ops->clear_allocated(table, index);
3785 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&table->lock, flags);
3786
3787 iommu_flush_irt(iommu, devid);
3788 iommu_completion_wait(iommu);
3789}

3938 BUG_ON(1);
3939 break;

3999static void irq_remapping_prepare_irte(struct amd_ir_data *data,
4000 struct irq_cfg *irq_cfg,
4001 struct irq_alloc_info *info,
4002 int devid, int index, int sub_handle)
4003{
4004 struct irq_2_irte *irte_info = &data->irq_2_irte;
4005 struct msi_msg *msg = &data->msi_entry;
4006 struct IO_APIC_route_entry *entry;
4007 struct amd_iommu *iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
4008
4009 if (!iommu)
4010 return;
4011
4012 data->irq_2_irte.devid = devid;
4013 data->irq_2_irte.index = index + sub_handle;
4014 iommu->irte_ops->prepare(data->entry, apic->irq_delivery_mode,
4015 apic->irq_dest_mode, irq_cfg->vector,
4016 irq_cfg->dest_apicid, devid);
4017
4018 switch (info->type) {
4019 case X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_IOAPIC:
4020 /* Setup IOAPIC entry */
4021 entry = info->ioapic_entry;
4022 info->ioapic_entry = NULL;
4023 memset(entry, 0, sizeof(*entry));
4024 entry->vector = index;
4025 entry->mask = 0;
4026 entry->trigger = info->ioapic_trigger;
4027 entry->polarity = info->ioapic_polarity;
4028 /* Mask level triggered irqs. */
4029 if (info->ioapic_trigger)
4030 entry->mask = 1;
4031 break;
4032
4033 case X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_HPET:
4034 case X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_MSI:
4035 case X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_MSIX:
4036 msg->address_hi = MSI_ADDR_BASE_HI;
4037 msg->address_lo = MSI_ADDR_BASE_LO;
4038 msg->data = irte_info->index;
4039 break;
4040
4041 default:
4042 BUG_ON(1);
4043 break;
4044 }
4045}
