4067static int irq_remapping_alloc(struct irq_domain *domain, unsigned int virq,
4068 unsigned int nr_irqs, void *arg)
4069{
4070 struct irq_alloc_info *info = arg;
4071 struct irq_data *irq_data;
4072 struct amd_ir_data *data = NULL;
4073 struct irq_cfg *cfg;
4074 int i, ret, devid;
4075 int index = -1;
4076
4077 if (!info)
4078 return -EINVAL;
4079 if (nr_irqs > 1 && info->type != X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_MSI &&
4080 info->type != X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_MSIX)
4081 return -EINVAL;
4082
4083 /*
4084 * With IRQ remapping enabled, don't need contiguous CPU vectors
4085 * to support multiple MSI interrupts.
4086 */
4087 if (info->type == X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_MSI)
4088 info->flags &= ~X86_IRQ_ALLOC_CONTIGUOUS_VECTORS;
4089
4090 devid = get_devid(info);
4091 if (devid < 0)
4092 return -EINVAL;
4093
4094 ret = irq_domain_alloc_irqs_parent(domain, virq, nr_irqs, arg);
4095 if (ret < 0)
4096 return ret;
4097
4098 if (info->type == X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_IOAPIC) {
4099 if (get_irq_table(devid, true))
4100 index = info->ioapic_pin;
4101 else
4102 ret = -ENOMEM;
4103 } else {
4104 index = alloc_irq_index(devid, nr_irqs);
4105 }
4106 if (index < 0) {
4107 pr_warn("Failed to allocate IRTE\n");
4108 ret = index;
4109 goto out_free_parent;
4110 }
4111
4112 for (i = 0; i < nr_irqs; i++) {
4113 irq_data = irq_domain_get_irq_data(domain, virq + i);
4114 cfg = irqd_cfg(irq_data);
4115 if (!irq_data || !cfg) {
4116 ret = -EINVAL;
4117 goto out_free_data;
4118 }
4119
4120 ret = -ENOMEM;
4121 data = kzalloc(sizeof(*data), GFP_KERNEL);
4122 if (!data)
4123 goto out_free_data;
4124
4125 if (!AMD_IOMMU_GUEST_IR_GA(amd_iommu_guest_ir))
4126 data->entry = kzalloc(sizeof(union irte), GFP_KERNEL);
4127 else
4128 data->entry = kzalloc(sizeof(struct irte_ga),
4129 GFP_KERNEL);
4130 if (!data->entry) {
4131 kfree(data);
4132 goto out_free_data;
4133 }
4134
4135 irq_data->hwirq = (devid << 16) + i;
4136 irq_data->chip_data = data;
4137 irq_data->chip = &amd_ir_chip;
4138 irq_remapping_prepare_irte(data, cfg, info, devid, index, i);
4139 irq_set_status_flags(virq + i, IRQ_MOVE_PCNTXT);
4140 }
4141
4142 return 0;
4143
4144out_free_data:
4145 for (i--; i >= 0; i--) {
4146 irq_data = irq_domain_get_irq_data(domain, virq + i);
4147 if (irq_data)
4148 kfree(irq_data->chip_data);
4149 }
4150 for (i = 0; i < nr_irqs; i++)
4151 free_irte(devid, index + i);
4152out_free_parent:
4153 irq_domain_free_irqs_common(domain, virq, nr_irqs);
4154 return ret;
4155}
4156
4157static void irq_remapping_free(struct irq_domain *domain, unsigned int virq,
4158 unsigned int nr_irqs)
4159{
4160 struct irq_2_irte *irte_info;
4161 struct irq_data *irq_data;
4162 struct amd_ir_data *data;
4163 int i;
4164
4165 for (i = 0; i < nr_irqs; i++) {
4166 irq_data = irq_domain_get_irq_data(domain, virq + i);
4167 if (irq_data && irq_data->chip_data) {
4168 data = irq_data->chip_data;
4169 irte_info = &data->irq_2_irte;
4170 free_irte(irte_info->devid, irte_info->index);
4171 kfree(data->entry);
4172 kfree(data);
4173 }
4174 }
4175 irq_domain_free_irqs_common(domain, virq, nr_irqs);
4176}

4209static int amd_ir_set_vcpu_affinity(struct irq_data *data, void *vcpu_info)
4210{
4211 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
4212 struct amd_iommu_pi_data *pi_data = vcpu_info;
4213 struct vcpu_data *vcpu_pi_info = pi_data->vcpu_data;
4214 struct amd_ir_data *ir_data = data->chip_data;
4215 struct irte_ga *irte = (struct irte_ga *) ir_data->entry;
4216 struct irq_2_irte *irte_info = &ir_data->irq_2_irte;
4217 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data = search_dev_data(irte_info->devid);
4218
4219 /* Note:
4220 * This device has never been set up for guest mode.
4221 * we should not modify the IRTE
4222 */
4223 if (!dev_data || !dev_data->use_vapic)
4224 return 0;
4225
4226 pi_data->ir_data = ir_data;
4227
4228 /* Note:
4229 * SVM tries to set up for VAPIC mode, but we are in
4230 * legacy mode. So, we force legacy mode instead.
4231 */
4232 if (!AMD_IOMMU_GUEST_IR_VAPIC(amd_iommu_guest_ir)) {
4233 pr_debug("AMD-Vi: %s: Fall back to using intr legacy remap\n",
4234 __func__);
4235 pi_data->is_guest_mode = false;
4236 }
4237
4238 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[irte_info->devid];
4239 if (iommu == NULL)
4240 return -EINVAL;
4241
4242 pi_data->prev_ga_tag = ir_data->cached_ga_tag;
4243 if (pi_data->is_guest_mode) {
4244 /* Setting */
4245 irte->hi.fields.ga_root_ptr = (pi_data->base >> 12);
4246 irte->hi.fields.vector = vcpu_pi_info->vector;
4247 irte->lo.fields_vapic.ga_log_intr = 1;
4248 irte->lo.fields_vapic.guest_mode = 1;
4249 irte->lo.fields_vapic.ga_tag = pi_data->ga_tag;
4250
4251 ir_data->cached_ga_tag = pi_data->ga_tag;
4252 } else {
4253 /* Un-Setting */
4254 struct irq_cfg *cfg = irqd_cfg(data);
4255
4256 irte->hi.val = 0;
4257 irte->lo.val = 0;
4258 irte->hi.fields.vector = cfg->vector;
4259 irte->lo.fields_remap.guest_mode = 0;
4260 irte->lo.fields_remap.destination = cfg->dest_apicid;
4261 irte->lo.fields_remap.int_type = apic->irq_delivery_mode;
4262 irte->lo.fields_remap.dm = apic->irq_dest_mode;
4263
4264 /*
4265 * This communicates the ga_tag back to the caller
4266 * so that it can do all the necessary clean up.
4267 */
4268 ir_data->cached_ga_tag = 0;
4269 }
4270
4271 return modify_irte_ga(irte_info->devid, irte_info->index, irte, ir_data);
4272}

4274static int amd_ir_set_affinity(struct irq_data *data,
4275 const struct cpumask *mask, bool force)
4276{
4277 struct amd_ir_data *ir_data = data->chip_data;
4278 struct irq_2_irte *irte_info = &ir_data->irq_2_irte;
4279 struct irq_cfg *cfg = irqd_cfg(data);
4280 struct irq_data *parent = data->parent_data;
4281 struct amd_iommu *iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[irte_info->devid];
4282 int ret;
4283
4284 if (!iommu)
4285 return -ENODEV;
4286
4287 ret = parent->chip->irq_set_affinity(parent, mask, force);
4288 if (ret < 0 || ret == IRQ_SET_MASK_OK_DONE)
4289 return ret;
4290
4291 /*
4292 * Atomically updates the IRTE with the new destination, vector
4293 * and flushes the interrupt entry cache.
4294 */
4295 iommu->irte_ops->set_affinity(ir_data->entry, irte_info->devid,
4296 irte_info->index, cfg->vector, cfg->dest_apicid);
4297
4298 /*
4299 * After this point, all the interrupts will start arriving
4300 * at the new destination. So, time to cleanup the previous
4301 * vector allocation.
4302 */
4303 send_cleanup_vector(cfg);
4304
4305 return IRQ_SET_MASK_OK_DONE;
4306}

4312 *msg = ir_data->msi_entry;

4323int amd_iommu_create_irq_domain(struct amd_iommu *iommu)
4324{
4325 struct fwnode_handle *fn;
4326
4327 fn = irq_domain_alloc_named_id_fwnode("AMD-IR", iommu->index);
4328 if (!fn)
4329 return -ENOMEM;
4330 iommu->ir_domain = irq_domain_create_tree(fn, &amd_ir_domain_ops, iommu);
4331 irq_domain_free_fwnode(fn);
4332 if (!iommu->ir_domain)
4333 return -ENOMEM;
4334
4335 iommu->ir_domain->parent = arch_get_ir_parent_domain();
4336 iommu->msi_domain = arch_create_remap_msi_irq_domain(iommu->ir_domain,
4337 "AMD-IR-MSI",
4338 iommu->index);
4339 return 0;
4340}
4341
4342int amd_iommu_update_ga(int cpu, bool is_run, void *data)
4343{
4344 unsigned long flags;
4345 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
4346 struct irq_remap_table *irt;
4347 struct amd_ir_data *ir_data = (struct amd_ir_data *)data;
4348 int devid = ir_data->irq_2_irte.devid;
4349 struct irte_ga *entry = (struct irte_ga *) ir_data->entry;
4350 struct irte_ga *ref = (struct irte_ga *) ir_data->ref;
4351
4352 if (!AMD_IOMMU_GUEST_IR_VAPIC(amd_iommu_guest_ir) ||
4353 !ref || !entry || !entry->lo.fields_vapic.guest_mode)
4354 return 0;
4355
4356 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
4357 if (!iommu)
4358 return -ENODEV;
4359
4360 irt = get_irq_table(devid, false);
4361 if (!irt)
4362 return -ENODEV;
4363
4364 spin_lock_irqsave(&irt->lock, flags);
4365
4366 if (ref->lo.fields_vapic.guest_mode) {
4367 if (cpu >= 0)
4368 ref->lo.fields_vapic.destination = cpu;
4369 ref->lo.fields_vapic.is_run = is_run;
4370 barrier();
4371 }
4372
4373 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&irt->lock, flags);
4374
4375 iommu_flush_irt(iommu, devid);
4376 iommu_completion_wait(iommu);
4377 return 0;
4378}
4379EXPORT_SYMBOL(amd_iommu_update_ga);
